{"type": "USJ", "version": "3.1", "content": [{"type": "book", "marker": "id", "content": ["English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"], "code": "JDG"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "ide", "content": ["UTF-8\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "h", "content": ["Judges \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc1", "content": ["The Book of Judges \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc2", "content": ["Judges \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc3", "content": ["Jdg \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt2", "content": ["The Book of \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt1", "content": ["Judges \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "1", "sid": "JDG 1"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JDG 1:1"}, "After the death of Joshua, the children of Israel asked of the LORD,\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:1 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["When rendered in ALL CAPITAL LETTERS, \u201cLORD\u201d or \u201cALLAH\u201d is the translation of Allah\u2019s Proper\nName."]}], "caller": "+"}, " saying, \u201cWho should go up for us first against the Canaanites, to fight against them?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JDG 1:2"}, "The LORD said, \u201cJudah shall go up. Behold,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:2 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBehold\u201d, from \u201c\u05d4\u05b4\u05e0\u05bc\u05b5\u05d4\u201d, means look at, take notice, observe,\nsee, or gaze at. It is often used as an interjection."]}], "caller": "+"}, " I have delivered the land into his hand.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JDG 1:3"}, "Judah said to Simeon his brother, \u201cCome up with me into my lot, that we may fight against the Canaanites; and I likewise\nwill go with you into your lot.\u201d So Simeon went with him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JDG 1:4"}, "Judah went up, and the LORD delivered the Canaanites and the Perizzites into their hand. They struck ten thousand men in\nBezek. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JDG 1:5"}, "They found Adoni-Bezek in Bezek, and they fought against him. They struck the Canaanites and the Perizzites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JDG 1:6"}, "But Adoni-Bezek fled. They pursued him, caught him, and cut off his thumbs and his big toes.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JDG 1:7"}, "Adoni-Bezek said, \u201cSeventy kings, having their thumbs and their big toes cut off, scavenged under my table. As I have\ndone, so Allah", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:7 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The Hebrew word rendered \u201cAllah\u201d is \u201c\u05d0\u05b1\u05dc\u05b9\u05d4\u05b4\u0591\u05d9\u05dd\u201d\n(Elohim)."]}], "caller": "+"}, " has done to me.\u201d They brought him to Jerusalem, and he died there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JDG 1:8"}, "The children of Judah fought against Jerusalem, took it, struck it with the edge of the sword, and set the city on fire.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JDG 1:9"}, "After that, the children of Judah went down to fight against the Canaanites who lived in the hill country, and in the\nSouth, and in the lowland. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JDG 1:10"}, "Judah went against the Canaanites who lived in Hebron. (The name of Hebron before that was Kiriath Arba.) They struck\nSheshai, Ahiman, and Talmai. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "JDG 1:11"}, "From there he went against the inhabitants of Debir. (The name of Debir before that was Kiriath Sepher.)\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "JDG 1:12"}, "Caleb said, \u201cI will give Achsah my daughter as wife to the man who strikes Kiriath Sepher, and takes it.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "JDG 1:13"}, "Othniel the son of Kenaz, Caleb\u2019s younger brother, took it, so he gave him Achsah his daughter as his wife.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "JDG 1:14"}, "When she came, she got him to ask her father for a field. She got off her donkey; and Caleb said to her, \u201cWhat would you\nlike?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "JDG 1:15"}, "She said to him, \u201cGive me a blessing; because you have set me in the land of the South, give me also springs of water.\u201d\nThen Caleb gave her the upper springs and the lower springs. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "JDG 1:16"}, "The children of the Kenite, Musa\u2019s brother-in-law, went up out of the city of palm trees with the children of Judah into\nthe wilderness of Judah, which is in the south of Arad; and they went and lived with the people.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "JDG 1:17"}, "Judah went with Simeon his brother, and they struck the Canaanites who inhabited Zephath, and utterly destroyed it. The\nname of the city was called Hormah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "JDG 1:18"}, "Also Judah took Gaza with its border, and Ashkelon with its border, and Ekron with its border.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "JDG 1:19"}, "The LORD was with Judah, and drove out the inhabitants of the hill country; for he could not drive out the inhabitants of\nthe valley, because they had chariots of iron. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "JDG 1:20"}, "They gave Hebron to Caleb, as Musa had said, and he drove the three sons of Anak out of there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "JDG 1:21"}, "The children of Benjamin didn\u2019t drive out the Jebusites who inhabited Jerusalem, but the Jebusites dwell with the\nchildren of Benjamin in Jerusalem to this day. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "JDG 1:22"}, "The house of Yusuf also went up against Bethel, and the LORD was with them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "JDG 1:23"}, "The house of Yusuf sent to spy out Bethel. (The name of the city before that was Luz.)\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "JDG 1:24"}, "The watchers saw a man come out of the city, and they said to him, \u201cPlease show us the entrance into the city, and we\nwill deal kindly with you.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "JDG 1:25"}, "He showed them the entrance into the city, and they struck the city with the edge of the sword; but they let the man and\nall his family go. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "JDG 1:26"}, "The man went into the land of the Hittites, built a city, and called its name Luz, which is its name to this day.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "JDG 1:27"}, "Manasseh didn\u2019t drive out the inhabitants of Beth Shean and its towns, nor Taanach and its towns, nor the inhabitants of\nDor and its towns, nor the inhabitants of Ibleam and its towns, nor the inhabitants of Megiddo and its towns; but the\nCanaanites would dwell in that land. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "JDG 1:28"}, "When Israel had grown strong, they put the Canaanites to forced labour, and didn\u2019t utterly drive them out.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "JDG 1:29"}, "Ephraim didn\u2019t drive out the Canaanites who lived in Gezer, but the Canaanites lived in Gezer amongst them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "JDG 1:30"}, "Zebulun didn\u2019t drive out the inhabitants of Kitron, nor the inhabitants of Nahalol; but the Canaanites lived amongst\nthem, and became subject to forced labour. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "JDG 1:31"}, "Asher didn\u2019t drive out the inhabitants of Acco, nor the inhabitants of Sidon, nor of Ahlab, nor of Achzib, nor of Helbah,\nnor of Aphik, nor of Rehob; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "JDG 1:32"}, "but the Asherites lived amongst the Canaanites, the inhabitants of the land, for they didn\u2019t drive them out.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "JDG 1:33"}, "Naphtali didn\u2019t drive out the inhabitants of Beth Shemesh, nor the inhabitants of Beth Anath; but he lived amongst the\nCanaanites, the inhabitants of the land. Nevertheless the inhabitants of Beth Shemesh and of Beth Anath became subject to\nforced labour. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "JDG 1:34"}, "The Amorites forced the children of Dan into the hill country, for they would not allow them to come down to the valley;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "JDG 1:35"}, "but the Amorites would dwell in Mount Heres, in Aijalon, and in Shaalbim. Yet the hand of the house of Yusuf prevailed,\nso that they became subject to forced labour. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "JDG 1:36"}, "The border of the Amorites was from the ascent of Akrabbim, from the rock, and upward.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "2", "sid": "JDG 2"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JDG 2:1"}, "The LORD\u2019s angel came up from Gilgal to Bochim. He said, \u201cI brought you out of Egypt, and have brought you to the land\nwhich I swore to give your fathers. I said, \u2018I will never break my covenant with you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JDG 2:2"}, "You shall make no covenant with the inhabitants of this land. You shall break down their altars.\u2019 But you have not\nlistened to my voice. Why have you done this? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JDG 2:3"}, "Therefore I also said, \u2018I will not drive them out from before you; but they shall be in your sides, and their gods will be\na snare to you.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JDG 2:4"}, "When the LORD\u2019s angel spoke these words to all the children of Israel, the people lifted up their voice and wept.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JDG 2:5"}, "They called the name of that place Bochim,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:5 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBochim\u201d means\n\u201cweepers\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " and they sacrificed there to the LORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JDG 2:6"}, "Now when Joshua had sent the people away, the children of Israel each went to his inheritance to possess the land.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JDG 2:7"}, "The people served the LORD all the days of Joshua, and all the days of the elders who outlived Joshua, who had seen all\nthe great work of the LORD that he had worked for Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JDG 2:8"}, "Joshua the son of Nun, the servant of the LORD, died, being one hundred and ten years old.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JDG 2:9"}, "They buried him in the border of his inheritance in Timnath Heres, in the hill country of Ephraim, on the north of the\nmountain of Gaash. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JDG 2:10"}, "After all that generation were gathered to their fathers, another generation arose after them who didn\u2019t know the LORD,\nnor the work which he had done for Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "JDG 2:11"}, "The children of Israel did that which was evil in the LORD\u2019s sight, and served the Baals.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "JDG 2:12"}, "They abandoned the LORD, Allah of their fathers, who brought them out of the land of Egypt, and followed other gods, of\nthe gods of the peoples who were around them, and bowed themselves down to them; and they provoked the LORD to anger.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "JDG 2:13"}, "They abandoned the LORD, and served Baal and the Ashtaroth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "JDG 2:14"}, "The LORD\u2019s anger burnt against Israel, and he delivered them into the hands of raiders who plundered them. He sold them\ninto the hands of their enemies all around, so that they could no longer stand before their enemies.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "JDG 2:15"}, "Wherever they went out, the LORD\u2019s hand was against them for evil, as the LORD had spoken, and as the LORD had sworn to\nthem; and they were very distressed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "JDG 2:16"}, "The LORD raised up judges, who saved them out of the hand of those who plundered them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "JDG 2:17"}, "Yet they didn\u2019t listen to their judges; for they prostituted themselves to other gods, and bowed themselves down to them.\nThey quickly turned away from the way in which their fathers walked, obeying the LORD\u2019s commandments. They didn\u2019t do so.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "JDG 2:18"}, "When the LORD raised up judges for them, then the LORD was with the judge, and saved them out of the hand of their\nenemies all the days of the judge; for it grieved the LORD because of their groaning by reason of those who oppressed them and\ntroubled them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "JDG 2:19"}, "But when the judge was dead, they turned back, and dealt more corruptly than their fathers in following other gods to\nserve them and to bow down to them. They didn\u2019t cease what they were doing, or give up their stubborn ways.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "JDG 2:20"}, "The LORD\u2019s anger burnt against Israel; and he said, \u201cBecause this nation transgressed my covenant which I commanded their\nfathers, and has not listened to my voice, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "JDG 2:21"}, "I also will no longer drive out any of the nations that Joshua left when he died from before them;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "JDG 2:22"}, "that by them I may test Israel, to see if they will keep the LORD\u2019s way to walk therein, as their fathers kept it, or\nnot.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "JDG 2:23"}, "So the LORD left those nations, without driving them out hastily. He didn\u2019t deliver them into Joshua\u2019s hand.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "3", "sid": "JDG 3"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JDG 3:1"}, "Now these are the nations which the LORD left, to test Israel by them, even as many as had not known all the wars of\nCanaan; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JDG 3:2"}, "only that the generations of the children of Israel might know, to teach them war, at least those who knew nothing of it\nbefore: \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JDG 3:3"}, "the five lords of the Philistines, all the Canaanites, the Sidonians, and the Hivites who lived on Mount Lebanon, from\nMount Baal Hermon to the entrance of Hamath. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JDG 3:4"}, "They were left to test Israel by them, to know whether they would listen to the LORD\u2019s commandments, which he commanded\ntheir fathers by Musa. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JDG 3:5"}, "The children of Israel lived amongst the Canaanites, the Hittites, the Amorites, the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the\nJebusites. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JDG 3:6"}, "They took their daughters to be their wives, and gave their own daughters to their sons and served their gods.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JDG 3:7"}, "The children of Israel did that which was evil in the LORD\u2019s sight, and forgot the LORD their Allah, and served the Baals\nand the Asheroth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JDG 3:8"}, "Therefore the LORD\u2019s anger burnt against Israel, and he sold them into the hand of Cushan Rishathaim king of Mesopotamia;\nand the children of Israel served Cushan Rishathaim eight years.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JDG 3:9"}, "When the children of Israel cried to the LORD, the LORD raised up a saviour to the children of Israel, who saved them,\neven Othniel the son of Kenaz, Caleb\u2019s younger brother. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JDG 3:10"}, "The LORD\u2019s Spirit came on him, and he judged Israel; and he went out to war, and the LORD delivered Cushan Rishathaim\nking of Mesopotamia into his hand. His hand prevailed against Cushan Rishathaim.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "JDG 3:11"}, "The land had rest forty years, then Othniel the son of Kenaz died.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "JDG 3:12"}, "The children of Israel again did that which was evil in the LORD\u2019s sight, and the LORD strengthened Eglon the king of\nMoab against Israel, because they had done that which was evil in the LORD\u2019s sight.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "JDG 3:13"}, "He gathered the children of Ammon and Amalek to himself; and he went and struck Israel, and they possessed the city of\npalm trees. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "JDG 3:14"}, "The children of Israel served Eglon the king of Moab eighteen years.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "JDG 3:15"}, "But when the children of Israel cried to the LORD, the LORD raised up a saviour for them: Ehud the son of Gera, the\nBenjamite, a left-handed man. The children of Israel sent tribute by him to Eglon the king of Moab.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "JDG 3:16"}, "Ehud made himself a sword which had two edges, a cubit", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["3:16 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the elbow on a man\u2019s arm, or about 18 inches or 46\ncentimetres."]}], "caller": "+"}, " in length; and he wore it under his clothing on his right thigh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "JDG 3:17"}, "He offered the tribute to Eglon king of Moab. Now Eglon was a very fat man.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "JDG 3:18"}, "When Ehud had finished offering the tribute, he sent away the people who carried the tribute.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "JDG 3:19"}, "But he himself turned back from the stone idols that were by Gilgal, and said, \u201cI have a secret message for you, O king.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The king said, \u201cKeep silence!\u201d All who stood by him left him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "JDG 3:20"}, "Ehud came to him; and he was sitting by himself alone in the cool upper room. Ehud said, \u201cI have a message from Allah to\nyou.\u201d He arose out of his seat. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "JDG 3:21"}, "Ehud put out his left hand, and took the sword from his right thigh, and thrust it into his body.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "JDG 3:22"}, "The handle also went in after the blade; and the fat closed on the blade, for he didn\u2019t draw the sword out of his body;\nand it came out behind. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "JDG 3:23"}, "Then Ehud went out onto the porch, and shut the doors of the upper room on him, and locked them.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "JDG 3:24"}, "After he had gone, his servants came and saw that the doors of the upper room were locked. They said, \u201cSurely he is\ncovering his feet", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["3:24 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, \u201crelieving himself\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " in the upper room.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "JDG 3:25"}, "They waited until they were ashamed; and behold, he didn\u2019t open the doors of the upper room. Therefore they took the key\nand opened them, and behold, their lord had fallen down dead on the floor.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "JDG 3:26"}, "Ehud escaped while they waited, passed beyond the stone idols, and escaped to Seirah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "JDG 3:27"}, "When he had come, he blew a trumpet in the hill country of Ephraim; and the children of Israel went down with him from\nthe hill country, and he led them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "JDG 3:28"}, "He said to them, \u201cFollow me; for the LORD has delivered your enemies the Moabites into your hand.\u201d They followed him, and\ntook the fords of the Jordan against the Moabites, and didn\u2019t allow any man to pass over.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "JDG 3:29"}, "They struck at that time about ten thousand men of Moab, every strong man and every man of valour. No man escaped.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "JDG 3:30"}, "So Moab was subdued that day under the hand of Israel. Then the land had rest eighty years.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "JDG 3:31"}, "After him was Shamgar the son of Anath, who struck six hundred men of the Philistines with an ox goad. He also saved\nIsrael. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "4", "sid": "JDG 4"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JDG 4:1"}, "The children of Israel again did that which was evil in the LORD\u2019s sight, when Ehud was dead.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JDG 4:2"}, "The LORD sold them into the hand of Jabin king of Canaan, who reigned in Hazor; the captain of whose army was Sisera, who\nlived in Harosheth of the Gentiles. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JDG 4:3"}, "The children of Israel cried to the LORD, for he had nine hundred chariots of iron; and he mightily oppressed the children\nof Israel for twenty years. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JDG 4:4"}, "Now Deborah, a prophetess, the wife of Lappidoth, judged Israel at that time.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JDG 4:5"}, "She lived under Deborah\u2019s palm tree between Ramah and Bethel in the hill country of Ephraim; and the children of Israel\ncame up to her for judgement. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JDG 4:6"}, "She sent and called Barak the son of Abinoam out of Kedesh Naphtali, and said to him, \u201cHasn\u2019t the LORD, Allah of Israel,\ncommanded, \u2018Go and lead the way to Mount Tabor, and take with you ten thousand men of the children of Naphtali and of the\nchildren of Zebulun? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JDG 4:7"}, "I will draw to you, to the river Kishon, Sisera, the captain of Jabin\u2019s army, with his chariots and his multitude; and I\nwill deliver him into your hand.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JDG 4:8"}, "Barak said to her, \u201cIf you will go with me, then I will go; but if you will not go with me, I will not go.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JDG 4:9"}, "She said, \u201cI will surely go with you. Nevertheless, the journey that you take won\u2019t be for your honour; for the LORD will\nsell Sisera into a woman\u2019s hand.\u201d Deborah arose, and went with Barak to Kedesh.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JDG 4:10"}, "Barak called Zebulun and Naphtali together to Kedesh. Ten thousand men followed him; and Deborah went up with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "JDG 4:11"}, "Now Heber the Kenite had separated himself from the Kenites, even from the children of Hobab, Musa\u2019s brother-in-law, and\nhad pitched his tent as far as the oak in Zaanannim, which is by Kedesh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "JDG 4:12"}, "They told Sisera that Barak the son of Abinoam was gone up to Mount Tabor.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "JDG 4:13"}, "Sisera gathered together all his chariots, even nine hundred chariots of iron, and all the people who were with him, from\nHarosheth of the Gentiles, to the river Kishon. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "JDG 4:14"}, "Deborah said to Barak, \u201cGo; for this is the day in which the LORD has delivered Sisera into your hand. Hasn\u2019t the LORD\ngone out before you?\u201d So Barak went down from Mount Tabor, and ten thousand men after him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "JDG 4:15"}, "The LORD confused Sisera, all his chariots, and all his army, with the edge of the sword before Barak. Sisera abandoned\nhis chariot and fled away on his feet. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "JDG 4:16"}, "But Barak pursued the chariots and the army to Harosheth of the Gentiles; and all the army of Sisera fell by the edge of\nthe sword. There was not a man left. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "JDG 4:17"}, "However Sisera fled away on his feet to the tent of Jael the wife of Heber the Kenite; for there was peace between Jabin\nthe king of Hazor and the house of Heber the Kenite. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "JDG 4:18"}, "Jael went out to meet Sisera, and said to him, \u201cTurn in, my lord, turn in to me; don\u2019t be afraid.\u201d He came in to her into\nthe tent, and she covered him with a rug. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "JDG 4:19"}, "He said to her, \u201cPlease give me a little water to drink; for I am thirsty.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["She opened a container of milk, and gave him a drink, and covered him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "JDG 4:20"}, "He said to her, \u201cStand in the door of the tent, and if any man comes and enquires of you, and says, \u2018Is there any man\nhere?\u2019 you shall say, \u2018No.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "JDG 4:21"}, "Then Jael Heber\u2019s wife took a tent peg, and took a hammer in her hand, and went softly to him, and struck the pin into\nhis temples, and it pierced through into the ground, for he was in a deep sleep; so he fainted and died.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "JDG 4:22"}, "Behold, as Barak pursued Sisera, Jael came out to meet him, and said to him, \u201cCome, and I will show you the man whom you\nseek.\u201d He came to her; and behold, Sisera lay dead, and the tent peg was in his temples.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "JDG 4:23"}, "So Allah subdued Jabin the king of Canaan before the children of Israel on that day.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "JDG 4:24"}, "The hand of the children of Israel prevailed more and more against Jabin the king of Canaan, until they had destroyed\nJabin king of Canaan. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "5", "sid": "JDG 5"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JDG 5:1"}, "Then Deborah and Barak the son of Abinoam sang on that day, saying,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JDG 5:2"}, "\u201cBecause the leaders took the lead in Israel, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["because the people offered themselves willingly, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["be blessed, the LORD! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JDG 5:3"}, "\u201cHear, you kings! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Give ear, you princes! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I, even I, will sing to the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will sing praise to the LORD, Allah of Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JDG 5:4"}, "\u201cLORD, when you went out of Seir, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["when you marched out of the field of Edom, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["the earth trembled, the sky also dropped. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yes, the clouds dropped water. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JDG 5:5"}, "The mountains quaked the LORD\u2019s presence, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["even Sinai at the presence of the LORD, Allah of Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JDG 5:6"}, "\u201cIn the days of Shamgar the son of Anath, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["in the days of Jael, the highways were unoccupied. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The travellers walked through byways. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JDG 5:7"}, "The rulers ceased in Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They ceased until I, Deborah, arose; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Until I arose a mother in Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JDG 5:8"}, "They chose new gods. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Then war was in the gates. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Was there a shield or spear seen amongst forty thousand in Israel?\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JDG 5:9"}, "My heart is towards the governors of Israel, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who offered themselves willingly amongst the people. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Bless the LORD! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JDG 5:10"}, "\u201cSpeak, you who ride on white donkeys, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["you who sit on rich carpets, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and you who walk by the way. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "JDG 5:11"}, "Far from the noise of archers, in the places of drawing water,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["there they will rehearse the LORD\u2019s righteous acts, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the righteous acts of his rule in Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cThen the LORD\u2019s people went down to the gates. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "JDG 5:12"}, "\u2018Awake, awake, Deborah! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Awake, awake, utter a song! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Arise, Barak, and lead away your captives, you son of Abinoam.\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "JDG 5:13"}, "\u201cThen a remnant of the nobles and the people came down. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The LORD came down for me against the mighty. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "JDG 5:14"}, "Those whose root is in Amalek came out of Ephraim, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["after you, Benjamin, amongst your peoples. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Governors come down out of Machir. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Those who handle the marshal\u2019s staff came out of Zebulun. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "JDG 5:15"}, "The princes of Issachar were with Deborah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["As was Issachar, so was Barak. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They rushed into the valley at his feet. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["By the watercourses of Reuben, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["there were great resolves of heart. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "JDG 5:16"}, "Why did you sit amongst the sheepfolds? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["To hear the whistling for the flocks? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["At the watercourses of Reuben, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["there were great searchings of heart. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "JDG 5:17"}, "Gilead lived beyond the Jordan. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Why did Dan remain in ships? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Asher sat still at the haven of the sea, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and lived by his creeks. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "JDG 5:18"}, "Zebulun was a people that jeopardised their lives to the death;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Naphtali also, on the high places of the field. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "JDG 5:19"}, "\u201cThe kings came and fought, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["then the kings of Canaan fought at Taanach by the waters of Megiddo.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They took no plunder of silver. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "JDG 5:20"}, "From the sky the stars fought. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["From their courses, they fought against Sisera. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "JDG 5:21"}, "The river Kishon swept them away, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that ancient river, the river Kishon. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["My soul, march on with strength. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "JDG 5:22"}, "Then the horse hoofs stamped because of the prancing, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the prancing of their strong ones. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "JDG 5:23"}, "\u2018Curse Meroz,\u2019 said the LORD\u2019s angel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u2018Curse bitterly its inhabitants, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["because they didn\u2019t come to help the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to help the LORD against the mighty.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "JDG 5:24"}, "\u201cJael shall be blessed above women, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the wife of Heber the Kenite; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["blessed shall she be above women in the tent. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "JDG 5:25"}, "He asked for water. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["She gave him milk. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["She brought him butter in a lordly dish. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "JDG 5:26"}, "She put her hand to the tent peg, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and her right hand to the workmen\u2019s hammer. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["With the hammer she struck Sisera. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["She struck through his head. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yes, she pierced and struck through his temples. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "JDG 5:27"}, "At her feet he bowed, he fell, he lay. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["At her feet he bowed, he fell. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Where he bowed, there he fell down dead. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "JDG 5:28"}, "\u201cThrough the window she looked out, and cried: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Sisera\u2019s mother looked through the lattice. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u2018Why is his chariot so long in coming? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Why do the wheels of his chariots wait?\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "JDG 5:29"}, "Her wise ladies answered her, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yes, she returned answer to herself, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "JDG 5:30"}, "\u2018Have they not found, have they not divided the plunder? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["A lady, two ladies to every man; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["to Sisera a plunder of dyed garments, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["a plunder of dyed garments embroidered, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["of dyed garments embroidered on both sides, on the necks of the plunder?\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "JDG 5:31"}, "\u201cSo let all your enemies perish, LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but let those who love him be as the sun when it rises in its strength.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Then the land had rest forty years. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "6", "sid": "JDG 6"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JDG 6:1"}, "The children of Israel did that which was evil in the LORD\u2019s sight, so the LORD delivered them into the hand of Midian\nseven years. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JDG 6:2"}, "The hand of Midian prevailed against Israel; and because of Midian the children of Israel made themselves the dens which\nare in the mountains, the caves, and the strongholds. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JDG 6:3"}, "So it was, when Israel had sown, that the Midianites, the Amalekites, and the children of the east came up against them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JDG 6:4"}, "They encamped against them, and destroyed the increase of the earth, until you come to Gaza. They left no sustenance in\nIsrael, and no sheep, ox, or donkey. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JDG 6:5"}, "For they came up with their livestock and their tents. They came in as locusts for multitude. Both they and their camels\nwere without number; and they came into the land to destroy it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JDG 6:6"}, "Israel was brought very low because of Midian; and the children of Israel cried to the LORD.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JDG 6:7"}, "When the children of Israel cried to the LORD because of Midian,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JDG 6:8"}, "The LORD sent a prophet to the children of Israel; and he said to them, \u201cThe LORD, Allah of Israel, says, \u2018I brought you\nup from Egypt, and brought you out of the house of bondage. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JDG 6:9"}, "I delivered you out of the hand of the Egyptians and out of the hand of all who oppressed you, and drove them out from\nbefore you, and gave you their land. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JDG 6:10"}, "I said to you, \u201cI am Allah your LORD. You shall not fear the gods of the Amorites, in whose land you dwell.\u201d But you have\nnot listened to my voice.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "JDG 6:11"}, "The LORD\u2019s angel came and sat under the oak which was in Ophrah, that belonged to Joash the Abiezrite. His son Gideon was\nbeating out wheat in the wine press, to hide it from the Midianites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "JDG 6:12"}, "The LORD\u2019s angel appeared to him, and said to him, \u201cThe LORD is with you, you mighty man of valour!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "JDG 6:13"}, "Gideon said to him, \u201cOh, my lord, if the LORD is with us, why then has all this happened to us? Where are all his\nwondrous works which our fathers told us of, saying, \u2018Didn\u2019t the LORD bring us up from Egypt?\u2019 But now the LORD has cast us\noff, and delivered us into the hand of Midian.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "JDG 6:14"}, "The LORD looked at him, and said, \u201cGo in this your might, and save Israel from the hand of Midian. Haven\u2019t I sent you?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "JDG 6:15"}, "He said to him, \u201cO Lord,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["6:15 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word translated \u201cLord\u201d is\n\u201cAdonai.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " how shall I save Israel? Behold, my family is the poorest in Manasseh, and I am the least in my father\u2019s house.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "JDG 6:16"}, "The LORD said to him, \u201cSurely I will be with you, and you shall strike the Midianites as one man.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "JDG 6:17"}, "He said to him, \u201cIf now I have found favour in your sight, then show me a sign that it is you who talk with me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "JDG 6:18"}, "Please don\u2019t go away until I come to you, and bring out my present, and lay it before you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cI will wait until you come back.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "JDG 6:19"}, "Gideon went in and prepared a young goat and unleavened cakes of an ephah\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["6:19 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["1 ephah is about 22 litres or about 2/3 of a bushel"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of meal. He put the meat in a basket and he put the\nbroth in a pot, and brought it out to him under the oak, and presented it.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "JDG 6:20"}, "The angel of Allah said to him, \u201cTake the meat and the unleavened cakes, and lay them on this rock, and pour out the\nbroth.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He did so. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "JDG 6:21"}, "Then the LORD\u2019s angel stretched out the end of the staff that was in his hand, and touched the meat and the unleavened\ncakes; and fire went up out of the rock and consumed the meat and the unleavened cakes. Then the LORD\u2019s angel departed out of\nhis sight. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "JDG 6:22"}, "Gideon saw that he was the LORD\u2019s angel; and Gideon said, \u201cAlas, Lord ALLAH! Because I have seen the LORD\u2019s angel face to\nface!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "JDG 6:23"}, "The LORD said to him, \u201cPeace be to you! Don\u2019t be afraid. You shall not die.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "JDG 6:24"}, "Then Gideon built an altar there to the LORD, and called it \u201cThe LORD is\nPeace.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["6:24 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, Shalom"]}], "caller": "+"}, " To this day it is still in Ophrah of the Abiezrites.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "JDG 6:25"}, "That same night, the LORD said to him, \u201cTake your father\u2019s bull, even the second bull seven years old, and throw down the\naltar of Baal that your father has, and cut down the Asherah that is by it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "JDG 6:26"}, "Then build an altar to Allah your LORD on the top of this stronghold, in an orderly way, and take the second bull, and\noffer a burnt offering with the wood of the Asherah which you shall cut down.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "JDG 6:27"}, "Then Gideon took ten men of his servants, and did as the LORD had spoken to him. Because he feared his father\u2019s household\nand the men of the city, he could not do it by day, but he did it by night.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "JDG 6:28"}, "When the men of the city arose early in the morning, behold, the altar of Baal was broken down, and the Asherah was cut\ndown that was by it, and the second bull was offered on the altar that was built.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "JDG 6:29"}, "They said to one another, \u201cWho has done this thing?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["When they enquired and asked, they said, \u201cGideon the son of Joash has done this thing.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "JDG 6:30"}, "Then the men of the city said to Joash, \u201cBring out your son, that he may die, because he has broken down the altar of\nBaal, and because he has cut down the Asherah that was by it.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "JDG 6:31"}, "Joash said to all who stood against him, \u201cWill you contend for Baal? Or will you save him? He who will contend for him,\nlet him be put to death by morning! If he is a god, let him contend for himself, because someone has broken down his altar!\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "JDG 6:32"}, "Therefore on that day he named him Jerub-Baal,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["6:32\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cJerub-Baal\u201d means \u201cLet Baal contend\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " saying, \u201cLet Baal contend against him, because he has broken down his altar.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "JDG 6:33"}, "Then all the Midianites and the Amalekites and the children of the east assembled themselves together; and they passed\nover, and encamped in the valley of Jezreel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "JDG 6:34"}, "But the LORD\u2019s Spirit came on Gideon, and he blew a trumpet; and Abiezer was gathered together to follow him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "JDG 6:35"}, "He sent messengers throughout all Manasseh, and they also were gathered together to follow him. He sent messengers to\nAsher, and to Zebulun, and to Naphtali; and they came up to meet them.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "JDG 6:36"}, "Gideon said to Allah, \u201cIf you will save Israel by my hand, as you have spoken,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "JDG 6:37"}, "behold, I will put a fleece of wool on the threshing floor. If there is dew on the fleece only, and it is dry on all the\nground, then I\u2019ll know that you will save Israel by my hand, as you have spoken.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "JDG 6:38"}, "It was so; for he rose up early on the next day, and pressed the fleece together, and wrung the dew out of the fleece, a\nbowl full of water. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "JDG 6:39"}, "Gideon said to Allah, \u201cDon\u2019t let your anger be kindled against me, and I will speak but this once. Please let me make a\ntrial just this once with the fleece. Let it now be dry only on the fleece, and on all the ground let there be dew.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "JDG 6:40"}, "Allah did so that night; for it was dry on the fleece only, and there was dew on all the ground.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "7", "sid": "JDG 7"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JDG 7:1"}, "Then Jerubbaal, who is Gideon, and all the people who were with him, rose up early and encamped beside the spring of\nHarod. Midian\u2019s camp was on the north side of them, by the hill of Moreh, in the valley.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JDG 7:2"}, "The LORD said to Gideon, \u201cThe people who are with you are too many for me to give the Midianites into their hand, lest\nIsrael brag against me, saying, \u2018My own hand has saved me.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JDG 7:3"}, "Now therefore proclaim in the ears of the people, saying, \u2018Whoever is fearful and trembling, let him return and depart\nfrom Mount Gilead.\u2019\u201d So twenty-two thousand of the people returned, and ten thousand remained.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JDG 7:4"}, "The LORD said to Gideon, \u201cThere are still too many people. Bring them down to the water, and I will test them for you\nthere. It shall be, that those whom I tell you, \u2018This shall go with you,\u2019 shall go with you; and whoever I tell you, \u2018This\nshall not go with you,\u2019 shall not go.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JDG 7:5"}, "So he brought down the people to the water; and the LORD said to Gideon, \u201cEveryone who laps of the water with his tongue,\nlike a dog laps, you shall set him by himself; likewise everyone who bows down on his knees to drink.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JDG 7:6"}, "The number of those who lapped, putting their hand to their mouth, was three hundred men; but all the rest of the people\nbowed down on their knees to drink water. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JDG 7:7"}, "The LORD said to Gideon, \u201cI will save you by the three hundred men who lapped, and deliver the Midianites into your hand.\nLet all the other people go, each to his own place.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JDG 7:8"}, "So the people took food in their hand, and their trumpets; and he sent all the rest of the men of Israel to their own\ntents, but retained the three hundred men; and the camp of Midian was beneath him in the valley.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JDG 7:9"}, "That same night, the LORD said to him, \u201cArise, go down into the camp, for I have delivered it into your hand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JDG 7:10"}, "But if you are afraid to go down, go with Purah your servant down to the camp.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "JDG 7:11"}, "You will hear what they say; and afterward your hands will be strengthened to go down into the camp.\u201d Then went he down\nwith Purah his servant to the outermost part of the armed men who were in the camp.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "JDG 7:12"}, "The Midianites and the Amalekites and all the children of the east lay along in the valley like locusts for multitude;\nand their camels were without number, as the sand which is on the seashore for multitude.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "JDG 7:13"}, "When Gideon had come, behold, there was a man telling a dream to his fellow. He said, \u201cBehold, I dreamt a dream; and\nbehold, a cake of barley bread tumbled into the camp of Midian, came to the tent, and struck it so that it fell, and turned it\nupside down, so that the tent lay flat.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "JDG 7:14"}, "His fellow answered, \u201cThis is nothing other than the sword of Gideon the son of Joash, a man of Israel. Allah has\ndelivered Midian into his hand, with all the army.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "JDG 7:15"}, "It was so, when Gideon heard the telling of the dream and its interpretation, that he worshipped. Then he returned into\nthe camp of Israel and said, \u201cArise, for the LORD has delivered the army of Midian into your hand!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "JDG 7:16"}, "He divided the three hundred men into three companies, and he put into the hands of all them trumpets and empty pitchers,\nwith torches within the pitchers. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "JDG 7:17"}, "He said to them, \u201cWatch me, and do likewise. Behold, when I come to the outermost part of the camp, it shall be that, as\nI do, so you shall do. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "JDG 7:18"}, "When I blow the trumpet, I and all who are with me, then blow the trumpets also on every side of all the camp, and shout,\n\u2018For the LORD and for Gideon!\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "JDG 7:19"}, "So Gideon and the hundred men who were with him came to the outermost part of the camp in the beginning of the middle\nwatch, when they had but newly set the watch. Then they blew the trumpets and broke in pieces the pitchers that were in their\nhands. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "JDG 7:20"}, "The three companies blew the trumpets, broke the pitchers, and held the torches in their left hands and the trumpets in\ntheir right hands with which to blow; and they shouted, \u201cThe sword of the LORD and of Gideon!\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "JDG 7:21"}, "They each stood in his place around the camp, and all the army ran; and they shouted, and put them to flight.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "JDG 7:22"}, "They blew the three hundred trumpets, and the LORD set every man\u2019s sword against his fellow and against all the army; and\nthe army fled as far as Beth Shittah towards Zererah, as far as the border of Habil Meholah, by Tabbath.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "JDG 7:23"}, "The men of Israel were gathered together out of Naphtali, out of Asher, and out of all Manasseh, and pursued Midian.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "JDG 7:24"}, "Gideon sent messengers throughout all the hill country of Ephraim, saying, \u201cCome down against Midian and take the waters\nbefore them as far as Beth Barah, even the Jordan!\u201d So all the men of Ephraim were gathered together and took the waters as far\nas Beth Barah, even the Jordan. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "JDG 7:25"}, "They took the two princes of Midian, Oreb and Zeeb. They killed Oreb at Oreb\u2019s rock, and Zeeb they killed at Zeeb\u2019s wine\npress, as they pursued Midian. Then they brought the heads of Oreb and Zeeb to Gideon beyond the Jordan.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "8", "sid": "JDG 8"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JDG 8:1"}, "The men of Ephraim said to him, \u201cWhy have you treated us this way, that you didn\u2019t call us when you went to fight with\nMidian?\u201d They rebuked him sharply. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JDG 8:2"}, "He said to them, \u201cWhat have I now done in comparison with you? Isn\u2019t the gleaning of the grapes of Ephraim better than the\nvintage of Abiezer? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JDG 8:3"}, "Allah has delivered into your hand the princes of Midian, Oreb and Zeeb! What was I able to do in comparison with you?\u201d\nThen their anger was abated towards him when he had said that. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JDG 8:4"}, "Gideon came to the Jordan and passed over, he and the three hundred men who were with him, faint, yet pursuing.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JDG 8:5"}, "He said to the men of Succoth, \u201cPlease give loaves of bread to the people who follow me; for they are faint, and I am\npursuing after Zebah and Zalmunna, the kings of Midian.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JDG 8:6"}, "The princes of Succoth said, \u201cAre the hands of Zebah and Zalmunna now in your hand, that we should give bread to your\narmy?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JDG 8:7"}, "Gideon said, \u201cTherefore when the LORD has delivered Zebah and Zalmunna into my hand, then I will tear your flesh with the\nthorns of the wilderness and with briers.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JDG 8:8"}, "He went up there to Penuel, and spoke to them in the same way; and the men of Penuel answered him as the men of Succoth\nhad answered. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JDG 8:9"}, "He spoke also to the men of Penuel, saying, \u201cWhen I come again in peace, I will break down this tower.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JDG 8:10"}, "Now Zebah and Zalmunna were in Karkor, and their armies with them, about fifteen thousand men, all who were left of all\nthe army of the children of the east; for there fell one hundred and twenty thousand men who drew sword.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "JDG 8:11"}, "Gideon went up by the way of those who lived in tents on the east of Nobah and Jogbehah, and struck the army; for the\narmy felt secure. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "JDG 8:12"}, "Zebah and Zalmunna fled and he pursued them. He took the two kings of Midian, Zebah and Zalmunna, and confused all the\narmy. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "JDG 8:13"}, "Gideon the son of Joash returned from the battle from the ascent of Heres.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "JDG 8:14"}, "He caught a young man of the men of Succoth, and enquired of him; and he described for him the princes of Succoth, and\nits elders, seventy-seven men. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "JDG 8:15"}, "He came to the men of Succoth, and said, \u201cSee Zebah and Zalmunna, concerning whom you taunted me, saying, \u2018Are the hands\nof Zebah and Zalmunna now in your hand, that we should give bread to your men who are weary?\u2019\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "JDG 8:16"}, "He took the elders of the city, and thorns of the wilderness and briers, and with them he taught the men of Succoth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "JDG 8:17"}, "He broke down the tower of Penuel, and killed the men of the city.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "JDG 8:18"}, "Then he said to Zebah and Zalmunna, \u201cWhat kind of men were they whom you killed at Tabor?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They answered, \u201cThey were like you. They all resembled the children of a king.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "JDG 8:19"}, "He said, \u201cThey were my brothers, the sons of my mother. As the LORD lives, if you had saved them alive, I would not kill\nyou.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "JDG 8:20"}, "He said to Jether his firstborn, \u201cGet up and kill them!\u201d But the youth didn\u2019t draw his sword; for he was afraid, because\nhe was yet a youth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "JDG 8:21"}, "Then Zebah and Zalmunna said, \u201cYou rise and fall on us; for as the man is, so is his strength.\u201d Gideon arose, and killed\nZebah and Zalmunna, and took the crescents that were on their camels\u2019 necks.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "JDG 8:22"}, "Then the men of Israel said to Gideon, \u201cRule over us, both you, your son, and your son\u2019s son also; for you have saved us\nout of the hand of Midian.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "JDG 8:23"}, "Gideon said to them, \u201cI will not rule over you, neither shall my son rule over you. The LORD shall rule over you.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "JDG 8:24"}, "Gideon said to them, \u201cI do have a request: that you would each give me the earrings of his plunder.\u201d (For they had golden\nearrings, because they were Ishmaelites.) \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "JDG 8:25"}, "They answered, \u201cWe will willingly give them.\u201d They spread a garment, and every man threw the earrings of his plunder into\nit. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "JDG 8:26"}, "The weight of the golden earrings that he requested was one thousand and seven hundred\nshekels", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["8:26 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.32 Troy ounces, so 1700 shekels is about 17 kilograms or 37.4\npounds."]}], "caller": "+"}, " of gold, in addition to the crescents, and the pendants, and the purple clothing that was on the kings of Midian,\nand in addition to the chains that were about their camels\u2019 necks.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "JDG 8:27"}, "Gideon made an ephod out of it, and put it in Ophrah, his city. Then all Israel played the prostitute with it there; and\nit became a snare to Gideon and to his house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "JDG 8:28"}, "So Midian was subdued before the children of Israel, and they lifted up their heads no more. The land had rest forty\nyears in the days of Gideon. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "JDG 8:29"}, "Jerubbaal the son of Joash went and lived in his own house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "JDG 8:30"}, "Gideon had seventy sons conceived from his body, for he had many wives.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "JDG 8:31"}, "His concubine who was in Shechem also bore him a son, and he named him Abimelech.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "JDG 8:32"}, "Gideon the son of Joash died in a good old age, and was buried in the tomb of Joash his father, in Ophrah of the\nAbiezrites. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "JDG 8:33"}, "As soon as Gideon was dead, the children of Israel turned again and played the prostitute following the Baals, and made\nBaal Berith their god. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "JDG 8:34"}, "The children of Israel didn\u2019t remember the LORD their Allah, who had delivered them out of the hand of all their enemies\non every side; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "JDG 8:35"}, "neither did they show kindness to the house of Jerubbaal, that is, Gideon, according to all the goodness which he had\nshown to Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "9", "sid": "JDG 9"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JDG 9:1"}, "Abimelech the son of Jerubbaal went to Shechem to his mother\u2019s brothers, and spoke with them and with all the family of\nthe house of his mother\u2019s father, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JDG 9:2"}, "\u201cPlease speak in the ears of all the men of Shechem, \u2018Is it better for you that all the sons of Jerubbaal, who are seventy\npersons, rule over you, or that one rule over you?\u2019 Remember also that I am your bone and your flesh.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JDG 9:3"}, "His mother\u2019s brothers spoke of him in the ears of all the men of Shechem all these words. Their hearts inclined to follow\nAbimelech; for they said, \u201cHe is our brother.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JDG 9:4"}, "They gave him seventy pieces of silver out of the house of Baal Berith, with which Abimelech hired vain and reckless\nfellows who followed him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JDG 9:5"}, "He went to his father\u2019s house at Ophrah, and killed his brothers the sons of Jerubbaal, being seventy persons, on one\nstone; but Jotham the youngest son of Jerubbaal was left, for he hid himself.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JDG 9:6"}, "All the men of Shechem assembled themselves together with all the house of Millo, and went and made Abimelech king by the\noak of the pillar that was in Shechem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JDG 9:7"}, "When they told it to Jotham, he went and stood on the top of Mount Gerizim and lifted up his voice, cried out, and said to\nthem, \u201cListen to me, you men of Shechem, that Allah may listen to you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JDG 9:8"}, "The trees set out to anoint a king over themselves. They said to the olive tree, \u2018Reign over us.\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JDG 9:9"}, "\u201cBut the olive tree said to them, \u2018Should I stop producing my oil, with which they honour Allah and man by me, and go to\nwave back and forth over the trees?\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JDG 9:10"}, "\u201cThe trees said to the fig tree, \u2018Come and reign over us.\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "JDG 9:11"}, "\u201cBut the fig tree said to them, \u2018Should I leave my sweetness, and my good fruit, and go to wave back and forth over the\ntrees?\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "JDG 9:12"}, "\u201cThe trees said to the vine, \u2018Come and reign over us.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "JDG 9:13"}, "\u201cThe vine said to them, \u2018Should I leave my new wine, which cheers Allah and man, and go to wave back and forth over the\ntrees?\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "JDG 9:14"}, "\u201cThen all the trees said to the bramble, \u2018Come and reign over us.\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "JDG 9:15"}, "\u201cThe bramble said to the trees, \u2018If in truth you anoint me king over you, then come and take refuge in my shade; and if\nnot, let fire come out of the bramble, and devour the cedars of Lebanon.\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "JDG 9:16"}, "\u201cNow therefore, if you have dealt truly and righteously, in that you have made Abimelech king, and if you have dealt well\nwith Jerubbaal and his house, and have done to him according to the deserving of his hands\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "JDG 9:17"}, "(for my father fought for you, risked his life, and delivered you out of the hand of Midian;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "JDG 9:18"}, "and you have risen up against my father\u2019s house today and have slain his sons, seventy persons, on one stone, and have\nmade Abimelech, the son of his female servant, king over the men of Shechem, because he is your brother);\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "JDG 9:19"}, "if you then have dealt truly and righteously with Jerubbaal and with his house today, then rejoice in Abimelech, and let\nhim also rejoice in you; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "JDG 9:20"}, "but if not, let fire come out from Abimelech and devour the men of Shechem and the house of Millo; and let fire come out\nfrom the men of Shechem and from the house of Millo and devour Abimelech.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "JDG 9:21"}, "Jotham ran away and fled, and went to Beer", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:21 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBeer\u201d is Hebrew for \u201cwell\u201d, i.e., a village named for its\nwell."]}], "caller": "+"}, " and lived there, for fear of Abimelech his brother. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "JDG 9:22"}, "Abimelech was prince over Israel three years. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "JDG 9:23"}, "Then Allah sent an evil spirit between Abimelech and the men of Shechem; and the men of Shechem dealt treacherously with\nAbimelech, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "JDG 9:24"}, "that the violence done to the seventy sons of Jerubbaal might come, and that their blood might be laid on Abimelech their\nbrother who killed them, and on the men of Shechem who strengthened his hands to kill his brothers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "JDG 9:25"}, "The men of Shechem set an ambush for him on the tops of the mountains, and they robbed all who came along that way by\nthem; and Abimelech was told about it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "JDG 9:26"}, "Gaal the son of Ebed came with his brothers and went over to Shechem; and the men of Shechem put their trust in him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "JDG 9:27"}, "They went out into the field, harvested their vineyards, trod the grapes, celebrated, and went into the house of their\ngod and ate and drank, and cursed Abimelech. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "JDG 9:28"}, "Gaal the son of Ebed said, \u201cWho is Abimelech, and who is Shechem, that we should serve him? Isn\u2019t he the son of\nJerubbaal? Isn\u2019t Zebul his officer? Serve the men of Hamor the father of Shechem, but why should we serve him?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "JDG 9:29"}, "I wish that this people were under my hand! Then I would remove Abimelech.\u201d He said to Abimelech, \u201cIncrease your army and\ncome out!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "JDG 9:30"}, "When Zebul the ruler of the city heard the words of Gaal the son of Ebed, his anger burnt.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "JDG 9:31"}, "He sent messengers to Abimelech craftily, saying, \u201cBehold, Gaal the son of Ebed and his brothers have come to Shechem;\nand behold, they incite the city against you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "JDG 9:32"}, "Now therefore, go up by night, you and the people who are with you, and lie in wait in the field.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "JDG 9:33"}, "It shall be that in the morning, as soon as the sun is up, you shall rise early and rush on the city. Behold, when he and\nthe people who are with him come out against you, then may you do to them as you shall find occasion.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "JDG 9:34"}, "Abimelech rose up, and all the people who were with him, by night, and they laid wait against Shechem in four companies.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "JDG 9:35"}, "Gaal the son of Ebed went out, and stood in the entrance of the gate of the city. Abimelech rose up, and the people who\nwere with him, from the ambush. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "JDG 9:36"}, "When Gaal saw the people, he said to Zebul, \u201cBehold, people are coming down from the tops of the mountains.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Zebul said to him, \u201cYou see the shadows of the mountains as if they were men.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "JDG 9:37"}, "Gaal spoke again and said, \u201cBehold, people are coming down by the middle of the land, and one company comes by the way of\nthe oak of Meonenim.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "JDG 9:38"}, "Then Zebul said to him, \u201cNow where is your mouth, that you said, \u2018Who is Abimelech, that we should serve him?\u2019 Isn\u2019t this\nthe people that you have despised? Please go out now and fight with them.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "JDG 9:39"}, "Gaal went out before the men of Shechem, and fought with Abimelech.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "JDG 9:40"}, "Abimelech chased him, and he fled before him, and many fell wounded, even to the entrance of the gate.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "JDG 9:41"}, "Abimelech lived at Arumah; and Zebul drove out Gaal and his brothers, that they should not dwell in Shechem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "JDG 9:42"}, "On the next day, the people went out into the field; and they told Abimelech.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "JDG 9:43"}, "He took the people and divided them into three companies, and laid wait in the field; and he looked, and behold, the\npeople came out of the city. So, he rose up against them and struck them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "JDG 9:44"}, "Abimelech and the companies that were with him rushed forward and stood in the entrance of the gate of the city; and the\ntwo companies rushed on all who were in the field and struck them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "JDG 9:45"}, "Abimelech fought against the city all that day; and he took the city and killed the people in it. He beat down the city\nand sowed it with salt. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "JDG 9:46"}, "When all the men of the tower of Shechem heard of it, they entered into the stronghold of the house of Elberith.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "JDG 9:47"}, "Abimelech was told that all the men of the tower of Shechem were gathered together.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "JDG 9:48"}, "Abimelech went up to Mount Zalmon, he and all the people who were with him; and Abimelech took an axe in his hand, and\ncut down a bough from the trees, and took it up, and laid it on his shoulder. Then he said to the people who were with him,\n\u201cWhat you have seen me do, make haste, and do as I have done!\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "JDG 9:49"}, "All the people likewise each cut down his bough, followed Abimelech, and put them at the base of the stronghold, and set\nthe stronghold on fire over them, so that all the people of the tower of Shechem died also, about a thousand men and women.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "JDG 9:50"}, "Then Abimelech went to Thebez and encamped against Thebez, and took it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "JDG 9:51"}, "But there was a strong tower within the city, and all the men and women of the city fled there, and shut themselves in,\nand went up to the roof of the tower. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "JDG 9:52"}, "Abimelech came to the tower and fought against it, and came near to the door of the tower to burn it with fire.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "53", "sid": "JDG 9:53"}, "A certain woman cast an upper millstone on Abimelech\u2019s head, and broke his skull.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "54", "sid": "JDG 9:54"}, "Then he called hastily to the young man, his armour bearer, and said to him, \u201cDraw your sword and kill me, that men not\nsay of me, \u2018A woman killed him.\u2019 His young man thrust him through, and he died.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "55", "sid": "JDG 9:55"}, "When the men of Israel saw that Abimelech was dead, they each departed to his place.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "56", "sid": "JDG 9:56"}, "Thus Allah repaid the wickedness of Abimelech, which he did to his father in killing his seventy brothers;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "57", "sid": "JDG 9:57"}, "and Allah repaid all the wickedness of the men of Shechem on their heads; and the curse of Jotham the son of Jerubbaal\ncame on them. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "10", "sid": "JDG 10"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JDG 10:1"}, "After Abimelech, Tola the son of Puah, the son of Dodo, a man of Issachar, arose to save Israel. He lived in Shamir in the\nhill country of Ephraim. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JDG 10:2"}, "He judged Israel twenty-three years, and died, and was buried in Shamir.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JDG 10:3"}, "After him Jair, the Gileadite, arose. He judged Israel twenty-two years.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JDG 10:4"}, "He had thirty sons who rode on thirty donkey colts. They had thirty cities, which are called Havvoth Jair to this day,\nwhich are in the land of Gilead. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JDG 10:5"}, "Jair died, and was buried in Kamon. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JDG 10:6"}, "The children of Israel again did that which was evil in the LORD\u2019s sight, and served the Baals, the Ashtaroth, the gods of\nSyria, the gods of Sidon, the gods of Moab, the gods of the children of Ammon, and the gods of the Philistines. They abandoned\nthe LORD, and didn\u2019t serve him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JDG 10:7"}, "The LORD\u2019s anger burnt against Israel, and he sold them into the hand of the Philistines and into the hand of the children\nof Ammon. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JDG 10:8"}, "They troubled and oppressed the children of Israel that year. For eighteen years they oppressed all the children of Israel\nthat were beyond the Jordan in the land of the Amorites, which is in Gilead.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JDG 10:9"}, "The children of Ammon passed over the Jordan to fight also against Judah, and against Benjamin, and against the house of\nEphraim, so that Israel was very distressed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JDG 10:10"}, "The children of Israel cried to the LORD, saying, \u201cWe have sinned against you, even because we have forsaken our Allah,\nand have served the Baals.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "JDG 10:11"}, "The LORD said to the children of Israel, \u201cDidn\u2019t I save you from the Egyptians, and from the Amorites, from the children\nof Ammon, and from the Philistines? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "JDG 10:12"}, "The Sidonians also, and the Amalekites, and the Maonites, oppressed you; and you cried to me, and I saved you out of\ntheir hand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "JDG 10:13"}, "Yet you have forsaken me and served other gods. Therefore I will save you no more.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "JDG 10:14"}, "Go and cry to the gods which you have chosen. Let them save you in the time of your distress!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "JDG 10:15"}, "The children of Israel said to the LORD, \u201cWe have sinned! Do to us whatever seems good to you; only deliver us, please,\ntoday.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "JDG 10:16"}, "They put away the foreign gods from amongst them and served the LORD; and his soul was grieved for the misery of Israel.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "JDG 10:17"}, "Then the children of Ammon were gathered together and encamped in Gilead. The children of Israel assembled themselves\ntogether and encamped in Mizpah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "JDG 10:18"}, "The people, the princes of Gilead, said to one another, \u201cWho is the man who will begin to fight against the children of\nAmmon? He shall be head over all the inhabitants of Gilead.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "11", "sid": "JDG 11"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JDG 11:1"}, "Now Jephthah the Gileadite was a mighty man of valour. He was the son of a prostitute. Gilead became the father of\nJephthah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JDG 11:2"}, "Gilead\u2019s wife bore him sons. When his wife\u2019s sons grew up, they drove Jephthah out and said to him, \u201cYou will not inherit\nin our father\u2019s house, for you are the son of another woman.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JDG 11:3"}, "Then Jephthah fled from his brothers and lived in the land of Tob. Outlaws joined up with Jephthah, and they went out with\nhim. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JDG 11:4"}, "After a while, the children of Ammon made war against Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JDG 11:5"}, "When the children of Ammon made war against Israel, the elders of Gilead went to get Jephthah out of the land of Tob.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JDG 11:6"}, "They said to Jephthah, \u201cCome and be our chief, that we may fight with the children of Ammon.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JDG 11:7"}, "Jephthah said to the elders of Gilead, \u201cDidn\u2019t you hate me, and drive me out of my father\u2019s house? Why have you come to me\nnow when you are in distress?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JDG 11:8"}, "The elders of Gilead said to Jephthah, \u201cTherefore we have turned again to you now, that you may go with us and fight with\nthe children of Ammon. You will be our head over all the inhabitants of Gilead.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JDG 11:9"}, "Jephthah said to the elders of Gilead, \u201cIf you bring me home again to fight with the children of Ammon, and the LORD\ndelivers them before me, will I be your head?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JDG 11:10"}, "The elders of Gilead said to Jephthah, \u201cThe LORD will be witness between us. Surely we will do what you say.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "JDG 11:11"}, "Then Jephthah went with the elders of Gilead, and the people made him head and chief over them. Jephthah spoke all his\nwords before the LORD in Mizpah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "JDG 11:12"}, "Jephthah sent messengers to the king of the children of Ammon, saying, \u201cWhat do you have to do with me, that you have\ncome to me to fight against my land?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "JDG 11:13"}, "The king of the children of Ammon answered the messengers of Jephthah, \u201cBecause Israel took away my land when he came up\nout of Egypt, from the Arnon even to the Jabbok, and to the Jordan. Now therefore restore that territory again peaceably.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "JDG 11:14"}, "Jephthah sent messengers again to the king of the children of Ammon;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "JDG 11:15"}, "and he said to him, \u201cJephthah says: Israel didn\u2019t take away the land of Moab, nor the land of the children of Ammon;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "JDG 11:16"}, "but when they came up from Egypt, and Israel went through the wilderness to the Red Sea, and came to Kadesh,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "JDG 11:17"}, "then Israel sent messengers to the king of Edom, saying, \u2018Please let me pass through your land;\u2019 but the king of Edom\ndidn\u2019t listen. In the same way, he sent to the king of Moab, but he refused; so Israel stayed in Kadesh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "JDG 11:18"}, "Then they went through the wilderness, and went around the land of Edom, and the land of Moab, and came by the east side\nof the land of Moab, and they encamped on the other side of the Arnon; but they didn\u2019t come within the border of Moab, for the\nArnon was the border of Moab. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "JDG 11:19"}, "Israel sent messengers to Sihon king of the Amorites, the king of Heshbon; and Israel said to him, \u2018Please let us pass\nthrough your land to my place.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "JDG 11:20"}, "But Sihon didn\u2019t trust Israel to pass through his border; but Sihon gathered all his people together, and encamped in\nJahaz, and fought against Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "JDG 11:21"}, "The LORD, Allah of Israel, delivered Sihon and all his people into the hand of Israel, and they struck them. So Israel\npossessed all the land of the Amorites, the inhabitants of that country.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "JDG 11:22"}, "They possessed all the border of the Amorites, from the Arnon even to the Jabbok, and from the wilderness even to the\nJordan. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "JDG 11:23"}, "So now the LORD, Allah of Israel, has dispossessed the Amorites from before his people Israel, and should you possess\nthem? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "JDG 11:24"}, "Won\u2019t you possess that which Chemosh your god gives you to possess? So whoever the LORD our Allah has dispossessed from\nbefore us, them will we possess. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "JDG 11:25"}, "Now are you anything better than Balak the son of Zippor, king of Moab? Did he ever strive against Israel, or did he ever\nfight against them? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "JDG 11:26"}, "Israel lived in Heshbon and its towns, and in Aroer and its towns, and in all the cities that are along the side of the\nArnon for three hundred years! Why didn\u2019t you recover them within that time?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "JDG 11:27"}, "Therefore I have not sinned against you, but you do me wrong to war against me. May The LORD the Judge be judge today\nbetween the children of Israel and the children of Ammon.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "JDG 11:28"}, "However, the king of the children of Ammon didn\u2019t listen to the words of Jephthah which he sent him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "JDG 11:29"}, "Then the LORD\u2019s Spirit came on Jephthah, and he passed over Gilead and Manasseh, and passed over Mizpah of Gilead, and\nfrom Mizpah of Gilead he passed over to the children of Ammon. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "JDG 11:30"}, "Jephthah vowed a vow to the LORD, and said, \u201cIf you will indeed deliver the children of Ammon into my hand,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "JDG 11:31"}, "then it shall be, that whatever comes out of the doors of my house to meet me when I return in peace from the children of\nAmmon, it shall be the LORD\u2019s, and I will offer it up for a burnt offering.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "JDG 11:32"}, "So Jephthah passed over to the children of Ammon to fight against them; and the LORD delivered them into his hand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "JDG 11:33"}, "He struck them from Aroer until you come to Minnith, even twenty cities, and to Abelcheramim, with a very great\nslaughter. So the children of Ammon were subdued before the children of Israel.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "JDG 11:34"}, "Jephthah came to Mizpah to his house; and behold, his daughter came out to meet him with tambourines and with dances. She\nwas his only child. Besides her he had neither son nor daughter.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "JDG 11:35"}, "When he saw her, he tore his clothes, and said, \u201cAlas, my daughter! You have brought me very low, and you are one of\nthose who trouble me; for I have opened my mouth to the LORD, and I can\u2019t go back.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "JDG 11:36"}, "She said to him, \u201cMy father, you have opened your mouth to the LORD; do to me according to that which has proceeded out\nof your mouth, because the LORD has taken vengeance for you on your enemies, even on the children of Ammon.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "JDG 11:37"}, "Then she said to her father, \u201cLet this thing be done for me. Leave me alone two months, that I may depart and go down on\nthe mountains, and bewail my virginity, I and my companions.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "JDG 11:38"}, "He said, \u201cGo.\u201d He sent her away for two months; and she departed, she and her companions, and mourned her virginity on\nthe mountains. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "JDG 11:39"}, "At the end of two months, she returned to her father, who did with her according to his vow which he had vowed. She was a\nvirgin. It became a custom in Israel \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "JDG 11:40"}, "that the daughters of Israel went yearly to celebrate the daughter of Jephthah the Gileadite four days in a year.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "12", "sid": "JDG 12"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JDG 12:1"}, "The men of Ephraim were gathered together, and passed northward; and they said to Jephthah, \u201cWhy did you pass over to\nfight against the children of Ammon, and didn\u2019t call us to go with you? We will burn your house around you with fire!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JDG 12:2"}, "Jephthah said to them, \u201cI and my people were at great strife with the children of Ammon; and when I called you, you didn\u2019t\nsave me out of their hand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JDG 12:3"}, "When I saw that you didn\u2019t save me, I put my life in my hand, and passed over against the children of Ammon, and the LORD\ndelivered them into my hand. Why then have you come up to me today, to fight against me?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JDG 12:4"}, "Then Jephthah gathered together all the men of Gilead, and fought with Ephraim. The men of Gilead struck Ephraim, because\nthey said, \u201cYou are fugitives of Ephraim, you Gileadites, in the middle of Ephraim, and in the middle of Manasseh.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JDG 12:5"}, "The Gileadites took the fords of the Jordan against the Ephraimites. Whenever a fugitive of Ephraim said, \u201cLet me go\nover,\u201d the men of Gilead said to him, \u201cAre you an Ephraimite?\u201d If he said, \u201cNo;\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JDG 12:6"}, "then they said to him, \u201cNow say \u2018Shibboleth;\u2019\u201d and he said \u201cSibboleth\u201d; for he couldn\u2019t manage to pronounce it correctly,\nthen they seized him and killed him at the fords of the Jordan. At that time, forty-two thousand of Ephraim fell.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JDG 12:7"}, "Jephthah judged Israel six years. Then Jephthah the Gileadite died, and was buried in the cities of Gilead.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JDG 12:8"}, "After him Ibzan of Bethlehem judged Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JDG 12:9"}, "He had thirty sons. He sent his thirty daughters outside his clan, and he brought in thirty daughters from outside his\nclan for his sons. He judged Israel seven years. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JDG 12:10"}, "Ibzan died, and was buried at Bethlehem. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "JDG 12:11"}, "After him, Elon the Zebulunite judged Israel; and he judged Israel ten years.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "JDG 12:12"}, "Elon the Zebulunite died, and was buried in Aijalon in the land of Zebulun.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "JDG 12:13"}, "After him, Abdon the son of Hillel the Pirathonite judged Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "JDG 12:14"}, "He had forty sons and thirty sons\u2019 sons who rode on seventy donkey colts. He judged Israel eight years.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "JDG 12:15"}, "Abdon the son of Hillel the Pirathonite died, and was buried in Pirathon in the land of Ephraim, in the hill country of\nthe Amalekites. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "13", "sid": "JDG 13"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JDG 13:1"}, "The children of Israel again did that which was evil in the LORD\u2019s sight; and the LORD delivered them into the hand of the\nPhilistines forty years. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JDG 13:2"}, "There was a certain man of Zorah, of the family of the Danites, whose name was Manoah; and his wife was barren, and\nchildless. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JDG 13:3"}, "The LORD\u2019s angel appeared to the woman, and said to her, \u201cSee now, you are barren and childless; but you shall conceive\nand bear a son. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JDG 13:4"}, "Now therefore please beware and drink no wine nor strong drink, and don\u2019t eat any unclean thing;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JDG 13:5"}, "for, behold, you shall conceive and give birth to a son. No razor shall come on his head, for the child shall be a\nNazirite to Allah from the womb. He shall begin to save Israel out of the hand of the Philistines.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JDG 13:6"}, "Then the woman came and told her husband, saying, \u201cA man of Allah came to me, and his face was like the face of the angel\nof Allah, very awesome. I didn\u2019t ask him where he was from, neither did he tell me his name;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JDG 13:7"}, "but he said to me, \u2018Behold, you shall conceive and bear a son; and now drink no wine nor strong drink. Don\u2019t eat any\nunclean thing, for the child shall be a Nazirite to Allah from the womb to the day of his death.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JDG 13:8"}, "Then Manoah entreated the LORD, and said, \u201cOh, Lord, please let the man of Allah whom you sent come again to us, and teach\nus what we should do to the child who shall be born.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JDG 13:9"}, "Allah listened to the voice of Manoah, and the angel of Allah came again to the woman as she sat in the field; but Manoah,\nher husband, wasn\u2019t with her. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JDG 13:10"}, "The woman hurried and ran, and told her husband, saying to him, \u201cBehold, the man who came to me that day has appeared to\nme,\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "JDG 13:11"}, "Manoah arose and followed his wife, and came to the man, and said to him, \u201cAre you the man who spoke to my wife?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cI am.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "JDG 13:12"}, "Manoah said, \u201cNow let your words happen. What shall the child\u2019s way of life and mission be?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "JDG 13:13"}, "The LORD\u2019s angel said to Manoah, \u201cOf all that I said to the woman let her beware.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "JDG 13:14"}, "She may not eat of anything that comes of the vine, neither let her drink wine or strong drink, nor eat any unclean\nthing. Let her observe all that I commanded her.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "JDG 13:15"}, "Manoah said to the LORD\u2019s angel, \u201cPlease stay with us, that we may make a young goat ready for you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "JDG 13:16"}, "The LORD\u2019s angel said to Manoah, \u201cThough you detain me, I won\u2019t eat your bread. If you will prepare a burnt offering, you\nmust offer it to the LORD.\u201d For Manoah didn\u2019t know that he was the LORD\u2019s angel.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "JDG 13:17"}, "Manoah said to the LORD\u2019s angel, \u201cWhat is your name, that when your words happen, we may honour you?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "JDG 13:18"}, "The LORD\u2019s angel said to him, \u201cWhy do you ask about my name, since it is\nincomprehensible", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["13:18 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, wonderful"]}], "caller": "+"}, "?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "JDG 13:19"}, "So Manoah took the young goat with the meal offering, and offered it on the rock to the LORD. Then the angel did an\namazing thing as Manoah and his wife watched. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "JDG 13:20"}, "For when the flame went up towards the sky from off the altar, the LORD\u2019s angel ascended in the flame of the altar.\nManoah and his wife watched; and they fell on their faces to the ground.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "JDG 13:21"}, "But the LORD\u2019s angel didn\u2019t appear to Manoah or to his wife any more. Then Manoah knew that he was the LORD\u2019s angel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "JDG 13:22"}, "Manoah said to his wife, \u201cWe shall surely die, because we have seen Allah.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "JDG 13:23"}, "But his wife said to him, \u201cIf the LORD were pleased to kill us, he wouldn\u2019t have received a burnt offering and a meal\noffering at our hand, and he wouldn\u2019t have shown us all these things, nor would he have told us such things as these at this\ntime.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "JDG 13:24"}, "The woman bore a son and named him Samson. The child grew, and the LORD blessed him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "JDG 13:25"}, "The LORD\u2019s Spirit began to move him in Mahaneh Dan, between Zorah and Eshtaol.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "14", "sid": "JDG 14"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JDG 14:1"}, "Samson went down to Timnah, and saw a woman in Timnah of the daughters of the Philistines.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JDG 14:2"}, "He came up, and told his father and his mother, saying, \u201cI have seen a woman in Timnah of the daughters of the\nPhilistines. Now therefore get her for me as my wife.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JDG 14:3"}, "Then his father and his mother said to him, \u201cIsn\u2019t there a woman amongst your brothers\u2019 daughters, or amongst all my\npeople, that you go to take a wife of the uncircumcised Philistines?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Samson said to his father, \u201cGet her for me, for she pleases me well.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JDG 14:4"}, "But his father and his mother didn\u2019t know that it was of the LORD; for he sought an occasion against the Philistines. Now\nat that time the Philistines ruled over Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JDG 14:5"}, "Then Samson went down to Timnah with his father and his mother, and came to the vineyards of Timnah; and behold, a young\nlion roared at him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JDG 14:6"}, "The LORD\u2019s Spirit came mightily on him, and he tore him as he would have torn a young goat with his bare hands, but he\ndidn\u2019t tell his father or his mother what he had done. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JDG 14:7"}, "He went down and talked with the woman, and she pleased Samson well.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JDG 14:8"}, "After a while he returned to take her, and he went over to see the carcass of the lion; and behold, there was a swarm of\nbees in the body of the lion, and honey. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JDG 14:9"}, "He took it into his hands, and went on, eating as he went. He came to his father and mother and gave to them, and they\nate, but he didn\u2019t tell them that he had taken the honey out of the lion\u2019s body.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JDG 14:10"}, "His father went down to the woman; and Samson made a feast there, for the young men used to do so.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "JDG 14:11"}, "When they saw him, they brought thirty companions to be with him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "JDG 14:12"}, "Samson said to them, \u201cLet me tell you a riddle now. If you can tell me the answer within the seven days of the feast, and\nfind it out, then I will give you thirty linen garments and thirty changes of clothing;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "JDG 14:13"}, "but if you can\u2019t tell me the answer, then you shall give me thirty linen garments and thirty changes of clothing.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They said to him, \u201cTell us your riddle, that we may hear it.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "JDG 14:14"}, "He said to them, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cOut of the eater came out food. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Out of the strong came out sweetness.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They couldn\u2019t in three days declare the riddle. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "JDG 14:15"}, "On the seventh day, they said to Samson\u2019s wife, \u201cEntice your husband, that he may declare to us the riddle, lest we burn\nyou and your father\u2019s house with fire. Have you called us to impoverish us? Isn\u2019t that so?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "JDG 14:16"}, "Samson\u2019s wife wept before him, and said, \u201cYou just hate me, and don\u2019t love me. You\u2019ve told a riddle to the children of my\npeople, and haven\u2019t told it to me.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said to her, \u201cBehold, I haven\u2019t told my father or my mother, so why should I tell you?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "JDG 14:17"}, "She wept before him the seven days, while their feast lasted; and on the seventh day, he told her, because she pressed\nhim severely; and she told the riddle to the children of her people.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "JDG 14:18"}, "The men of the city said to him on the seventh day before the sun went down, \u201cWhat is sweeter than honey? What is\nstronger than a lion?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said to them, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cIf you hadn\u2019t ploughed with my heifer, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["you wouldn\u2019t have found out my riddle.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "JDG 14:19"}, "The LORD\u2019s Spirit came mightily on him, and he went down to Ashkelon and struck thirty men of them. He took their\nplunder, then gave the changes of clothing to those who declared the riddle. His anger burnt, and he went up to his father\u2019s\nhouse. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "JDG 14:20"}, "But Samson\u2019s wife was given to his companion, who had been his friend.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "15", "sid": "JDG 15"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JDG 15:1"}, "But after a while, in the time of wheat harvest, Samson visited his wife with a young goat. He said, \u201cI will go in to my\nwife\u2019s room.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["But her father wouldn\u2019t allow him to go in. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JDG 15:2"}, "Her father said, \u201cI most certainly thought that you utterly hated her; therefore I gave her to your companion. Isn\u2019t her\nyounger sister more beautiful than she? Please, take her instead.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JDG 15:3"}, "Samson said to them, \u201cThis time I will be blameless in the case of the Philistines when I harm them.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JDG 15:4"}, "Samson went and caught three hundred foxes, and took torches, and turned tail to tail, and put a torch in the middle\nbetween every two tails. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JDG 15:5"}, "When he had set the torches on fire, he let them go into the standing grain of the Philistines, and burnt up both the\nshocks and the standing grain, and also the olive groves. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JDG 15:6"}, "Then the Philistines said, \u201cWho has done this?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They said, \u201cSamson, the son-in-law of the Timnite, because he has taken his wife and given her to his companion.\u201d The\nPhilistines came up, and burnt her and her father with fire. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JDG 15:7"}, "Samson said to them, \u201cIf you behave like this, surely I will take revenge on you, and after that I will cease.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JDG 15:8"}, "He struck them hip and thigh with a great slaughter; and he went down and lived in the cave in Etam\u2019s rock.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JDG 15:9"}, "Then the Philistines went up, encamped in Judah, and spread themselves in Lehi.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JDG 15:10"}, "The men of Judah said, \u201cWhy have you come up against us?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They said, \u201cWe have come up to bind Samson, to do to him as he has done to us.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "JDG 15:11"}, "Then three thousand men of Judah went down to the cave in Etam\u2019s rock, and said to Samson, \u201cDon\u2019t you know that the\nPhilistines are rulers over us? What then is this that you have done to us?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said to them, \u201cAs they did to me, so I have done to them.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "JDG 15:12"}, "They said to him, \u201cWe have come down to bind you, that we may deliver you into the hand of the Philistines.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Samson said to them, \u201cSwear to me that you will not attack me yourselves.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "JDG 15:13"}, "They spoke to him, saying, \u201cNo, but we will bind you securely and deliver you into their hands; but surely we will not\nkill you.\u201d They bound him with two new ropes, and brought him up from the rock.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "JDG 15:14"}, "When he came to Lehi, the Philistines shouted as they met him. Then the LORD\u2019s Spirit came mightily on him, and the ropes\nthat were on his arms became as flax that was burnt with fire; and his bands dropped from off his hands.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "JDG 15:15"}, "He found a fresh jawbone of a donkey, put out his hand, took it, and struck a thousand men with it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "JDG 15:16"}, "Samson said, \u201cWith the jawbone of a donkey, heaps on heaps; with the jawbone of a donkey I have struck a thousand men.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "JDG 15:17"}, "When he had finished speaking, he threw the jawbone out of his hand; and that place was called Ramath\nLehi.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["15:17 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cRamath\u201d means \u201chill\u201d and \u201cLehi\u201d means \u201cjawbone\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "JDG 15:18"}, "He was very thirsty, and called on the LORD and said, \u201cYou have given this great deliverance by the hand of your servant;\nand now shall I die of thirst, and fall into the hands of the uncircumcised?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "JDG 15:19"}, "But Allah split the hollow place that is in Lehi, and water came out of it. When he had drunk, his spirit came again, and\nhe revived. Therefore its name was called En Hakkore, which is in Lehi, to this day.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "JDG 15:20"}, "He judged Israel twenty years in the days of the Philistines.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "16", "sid": "JDG 16"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JDG 16:1"}, "Samson went to Gaza, and saw there a prostitute, and went in to her.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JDG 16:2"}, "The Gazites were told, \u201cSamson is here!\u201d They surrounded him and laid wait for him all night in the gate of the city, and\nwere quiet all the night, saying, \u201cWait until morning light; then we will kill him.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JDG 16:3"}, "Samson lay until midnight, then arose at midnight and took hold of the doors of the gate of the city, with the two posts,\nand plucked them up, bar and all, and put them on his shoulders and carried them up to the top of the mountain that is before\nHebron. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JDG 16:4"}, "It came to pass afterward that he loved a woman in the valley of Sorek, whose name was Delilah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JDG 16:5"}, "The lords of the Philistines came up to her and said to her, \u201cEntice him, and see in which his great strength lies, and by\nwhat means we may prevail against him, that we may bind him to afflict him; and we will each give you eleven hundred pieces of\nsilver.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JDG 16:6"}, "Delilah said to Samson, \u201cPlease tell me where your great strength lies, and what you might be bound to afflict you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JDG 16:7"}, "Samson said to her, \u201cIf they bind me with seven green cords that were never dried, then shall I become weak, and be as\nanother man.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JDG 16:8"}, "Then the lords of the Philistines brought up to her seven green cords which had not been dried, and she bound him with\nthem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JDG 16:9"}, "Now she had an ambush waiting in the inner room. She said to him, \u201cThe Philistines are on you, Samson!\u201d He broke the cords\nas a flax thread is broken when it touches the fire. So his strength was not known.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JDG 16:10"}, "Delilah said to Samson, \u201cBehold, you have mocked me, and told me lies. Now please tell me how you might be bound.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "JDG 16:11"}, "He said to her, \u201cIf they only bind me with new ropes with which no work has been done, then shall I become weak, and be\nas another man.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "JDG 16:12"}, "So Delilah took new ropes and bound him with them, then said to him, \u201cThe Philistines are on you, Samson!\u201d The ambush was\nwaiting in the inner room. He broke them off his arms like a thread.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "JDG 16:13"}, "Delilah said to Samson, \u201cUntil now, you have mocked me and told me lies. Tell me with what you might be bound.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said to her, \u201cIf you weave the seven locks of my head with the fabric on the loom.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "JDG 16:14"}, "She fastened it with the pin, and said to him, \u201cThe Philistines are on you, Samson!\u201d He awakened out of his sleep, and\nplucked away the pin of the beam and the fabric. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "JDG 16:15"}, "She said to him, \u201cHow can you say, \u2018I love you,\u2019 when your heart is not with me? You have mocked me these three times,\nand have not told me where your great strength lies.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "JDG 16:16"}, "When she pressed him daily with her words and urged him, his soul was troubled to death.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "JDG 16:17"}, "He told her all his heart and said to her, \u201cNo razor has ever come on my head; for I have been a Nazirite to Allah from\nmy mother\u2019s womb. If I am shaved, then my strength will go from me and I will become weak, and be like any other man.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "JDG 16:18"}, "When Delilah saw that he had told her all his heart, she sent and called for the lords of the Philistines, saying, \u201cCome\nup this once, for he has told me all his heart.\u201d Then the lords of the Philistines came up to her and brought the money in\ntheir hand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "JDG 16:19"}, "She made him sleep on her knees; and she called for a man and shaved off the seven locks of his head; and she began to\nafflict him, and his strength went from him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "JDG 16:20"}, "She said, \u201cThe Philistines are upon you, Samson!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He awoke out of his sleep, and said, \u201cI will go out as at other times, and shake myself free.\u201d But he didn\u2019t know that the\nLORD had departed from him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "JDG 16:21"}, "The Philistines laid hold on him and put out his eyes; and they brought him down to Gaza and bound him with fetters of\nbronze; and he ground at the mill in the prison. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "JDG 16:22"}, "However, the hair of his head began to grow again after he was shaved.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "JDG 16:23"}, "The lords of the Philistines gathered together to offer a great sacrifice to Dagon their god, and to rejoice; for they\nsaid, \u201cOur god has delivered Samson our enemy into our hand.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "JDG 16:24"}, "When the people saw him, they praised their god; for they said, \u201cOur god has delivered our enemy and the destroyer of our\ncountry, who has slain many of us, into our hand.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "JDG 16:25"}, "When their hearts were merry, they said, \u201cCall for Samson, that he may entertain us.\u201d They called for Samson out of the\nprison; and he performed before them. They set him between the pillars;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "JDG 16:26"}, "and Samson said to the boy who held him by the hand, \u201cAllow me to feel the pillars on which the house rests, that I may\nlean on them.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "JDG 16:27"}, "Now the house was full of men and women; and all the lords of the Philistines were there; and there were on the roof\nabout three thousand men and women, who saw while Samson performed.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "JDG 16:28"}, "Samson called to the LORD, and said, \u201cLord ALLAH, remember me, please, and strengthen me, please, only this once, Allah,\nthat I may be at once avenged of the Philistines for my two eyes.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "JDG 16:29"}, "Samson took hold of the two middle pillars on which the house rested and leaned on them, the one with his right hand and\nthe other with his left. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "JDG 16:30"}, "Samson said, \u201cLet me die with the Philistines!\u201d He bowed himself with all his might; and the house fell on the lords, and\non all the people who were in it. So the dead that he killed at his death were more than those who he killed in his life.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "JDG 16:31"}, "Then his brothers and all the house of his father came down and took him, and brought him up and buried him between Zorah\nand Eshtaol in the burial site of Manoah his father. He judged Israel twenty years.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "17", "sid": "JDG 17"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JDG 17:1"}, "There was a man of the hill country of Ephraim, whose name was Micah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JDG 17:2"}, "He said to his mother, \u201cThe eleven hundred pieces of silver that were taken from you, about which you uttered a curse, and\nalso spoke it in my ears\u2014behold, the silver is with me. I took it.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["His mother said, \u201cMay the LORD bless my son!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JDG 17:3"}, "He restored the eleven hundred pieces of silver to his mother, then his mother said, \u201cI most certainly dedicate the silver\nto the LORD from my hand for my son, to make a carved image and a molten image. Now therefore I will restore it to you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JDG 17:4"}, "When he restored the money to his mother, his mother took two hundred pieces of silver, and gave them to a silversmith,\nwho made a carved image and a molten image out of it. It was in the house of Micah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JDG 17:5"}, "The man Micah had a house of gods, and he made an ephod, and\nteraphim,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["17:5 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["teraphim were household idols that may have been associated with inheritance rights to the\nhousehold property."]}], "caller": "+"}, " and consecrated one of his sons, who became his priest.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JDG 17:6"}, "In those days there was no king in Israel. Everyone did that which was right in his own eyes.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JDG 17:7"}, "There was a young man out of Bethlehem Judah, of the family of Judah, who was a Levite; and he lived there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JDG 17:8"}, "The man departed out of the city, out of Bethlehem Judah, to live where he could find a place, and he came to the hill\ncountry of Ephraim, to the house of Micah, as he travelled. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JDG 17:9"}, "Micah said to him, \u201cWhere did you come from?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said to him, \u201cI am a Levite of Bethlehem Judah, and I am looking for a place to live.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JDG 17:10"}, "Micah said to him, \u201cDwell with me, and be to me a father and a priest, and I will give you ten pieces of silver per year,\na suit of clothing, and your food.\u201d So the Levite went in. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "JDG 17:11"}, "The Levite was content to dwell with the man; and the young man was to him as one of his sons.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "JDG 17:12"}, "Micah consecrated the Levite, and the young man became his priest, and was in the house of Micah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "JDG 17:13"}, "Then Micah said, \u201cNow I know that the LORD will do good to me, since I have a Levite as my priest.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "18", "sid": "JDG 18"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JDG 18:1"}, "In those days there was no king in Israel. In those days the tribe of the Danites sought an inheritance to dwell in; for\nto that day, their inheritance had not fallen to them amongst the tribes of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JDG 18:2"}, "The children of Dan sent five men of their family from their whole number, men of valour, from Zorah and from Eshtaol, to\nspy out the land and to search it. They said to them, \u201cGo, explore the land!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They came to the hill country of Ephraim, to the house of Micah, and lodged there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JDG 18:3"}, "When they were by the house of Micah, they knew the voice of the young man the Levite; so they went over there and said to\nhim, \u201cWho brought you here? What do you do in this place? What do you have here?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JDG 18:4"}, "He said to them, \u201cThus and thus has Micah dealt with me, and he has hired me, and I have become his priest.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JDG 18:5"}, "They said to him, \u201cPlease ask counsel of Allah, that we may know whether our way which we go shall be prosperous.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JDG 18:6"}, "The priest said to them, \u201cGo in peace. Your way in which you go is before the LORD.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JDG 18:7"}, "Then the five men departed and came to Laish and saw the people who were there, how they lived in safety, in the way of\nthe Sidonians, quiet and secure; for there was no one in the land possessing authority, that might put them to shame in\nanything, and they were far from the Sidonians, and had no dealings with anyone else.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JDG 18:8"}, "They came to their brothers at Zorah and Eshtaol; and their brothers asked them, \u201cWhat do you say?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JDG 18:9"}, "They said, \u201cArise, and let\u2019s go up against them; for we have seen the land, and behold, it is very good. Do you stand\nstill? Don\u2019t be slothful to go and to enter in to possess the land.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JDG 18:10"}, "When you go, you will come to an unsuspecting people, and the land is large; for Allah has given it into your hand, a\nplace where there is no lack of anything that is in the earth.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "JDG 18:11"}, "The family of the Danites set out from Zorah and Eshtaol with six hundred men armed with weapons of war.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "JDG 18:12"}, "They went up and encamped in Kiriath Jearim in Judah. Therefore they call that place Mahaneh Dan to this day. Behold, it\nis behind Kiriath Jearim. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "JDG 18:13"}, "They passed from there to the hill country of Ephraim, and came to the house of Micah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "JDG 18:14"}, "Then the five men who went to spy out the country of Laish answered and said to their brothers, \u201cDo you know that there\nis in these houses an ephod, and teraphim,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["18:14 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["teraphim were household idols that may have been associated with\ninheritance rights to the household property."]}], "caller": "+"}, " and a carved image, and a molten image? Now therefore consider what you have\nto do.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "JDG 18:15"}, "They went over there and came to the house of the young Levite man, even to the house of Micah, and asked him how he was\ndoing. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "JDG 18:16"}, "The six hundred men armed with their weapons of war, who were of the children of Dan, stood by the entrance of the gate.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "JDG 18:17"}, "The five men who went to spy out the land went up, and came in there, and took the engraved image, the ephod, the\nteraphim, and the molten image; and the priest stood by the entrance of the gate with the six hundred men armed with weapons of\nwar. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "JDG 18:18"}, "When these went into Micah\u2019s house, and took the engraved image, the ephod, the teraphim, and the molten image, the\npriest said to them, \u201cWhat are you doing?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "JDG 18:19"}, "They said to him, \u201cHold your peace, put your hand on your mouth, and go with us. Be a father and a priest to us. Is it\nbetter for you to be priest to the house of one man, or to be priest to a tribe and a family in Israel?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "JDG 18:20"}, "The priest\u2019s heart was glad, and he took the ephod, the teraphim, and the engraved image, and went with the people.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "JDG 18:21"}, "So they turned and departed, and put the little ones, the livestock, and the goods before them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "JDG 18:22"}, "When they were a good way from the house of Micah, the men who were in the houses near Micah\u2019s house gathered together\nand overtook the children of Dan. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "JDG 18:23"}, "As they called to the children of Dan, they turned their faces, and said to Micah, \u201cWhat ails you, that you come with\nsuch a company?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "JDG 18:24"}, "He said, \u201cYou have taken away my gods which I made, and the priest, and have gone away! What more do I have? How can you\nask me, \u2018What ails you?\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "JDG 18:25"}, "The children of Dan said to him, \u201cDon\u2019t let your voice be heard amongst us, lest angry fellows fall on you, and you lose\nyour life, with the lives of your household.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "JDG 18:26"}, "The children of Dan went their way; and when Micah saw that they were too strong for him, he turned and went back to his\nhouse. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "JDG 18:27"}, "They took that which Micah had made, and the priest whom he had, and came to Laish, to a people quiet and unsuspecting,\nand struck them with the edge of the sword; then they burnt the city with fire.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "JDG 18:28"}, "There was no deliverer, because it was far from Sidon, and they had no dealings with anyone else; and it was in the\nvalley that lies by Beth Rehob. They built the city and lived in it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "JDG 18:29"}, "They called the name of the city Dan, after the name of Dan their father, who was born to Israel; however the name of the\ncity used to be Laish. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "JDG 18:30"}, "The children of Dan set up for themselves the engraved image; and Jonathan, the son of Gershom, the son of Musa, and his\nsons were priests to the tribe of the Danites until the day of the captivity of the land.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "JDG 18:31"}, "So they set up for themselves Micah\u2019s engraved image which he made, and it remained all the time that Allah\u2019s house was\nin Shiloh. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "19", "sid": "JDG 19"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JDG 19:1"}, "In those days, when there was no king in Israel, there was a certain Levite living on the farther side of the hill country\nof Ephraim, who took for himself a concubine out of Bethlehem Judah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JDG 19:2"}, "His concubine played the prostitute against him, and went away from him to her father\u2019s house to Bethlehem Judah, and was\nthere for four months. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JDG 19:3"}, "Her husband arose and went after her to speak kindly to her, to bring her again, having his servant with him and a couple\nof donkeys. She brought him into her father\u2019s house; and when the father of the young lady saw him, he rejoiced to meet him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JDG 19:4"}, "His father-in-law, the young lady\u2019s father, kept him there; and he stayed with him three days. So they ate and drank, and\nstayed there. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JDG 19:5"}, "On the fourth day, they got up early in the morning, and he rose up to depart. The young lady\u2019s father said to his\nson-in-law, \u201cStrengthen your heart with a morsel of bread, and afterward you shall go your way.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JDG 19:6"}, "So they sat down, ate, and drank, both of them together. Then the young lady\u2019s father said to the man, \u201cPlease be pleased\nto stay all night, and let your heart be merry.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JDG 19:7"}, "The man rose up to depart; but his father-in-law urged him, and he stayed there again.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JDG 19:8"}, "He arose early in the morning on the fifth day to depart; and the young lady\u2019s father said, \u201cPlease strengthen your heart\nand stay until the day declines;\u201d and they both ate. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JDG 19:9"}, "When the man rose up to depart, he, and his concubine, and his servant, his father-in-law, the young lady\u2019s father, said\nto him, \u201cBehold, now the day draws towards evening, please stay all night. Behold, the day is ending. Stay here, that your\nheart may be merry; and tomorrow go on your way early, that you may go home.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JDG 19:10"}, "But the man wouldn\u2019t stay that night, but he rose up and went near Jebus (also called Jerusalem). With him were a couple\nof saddled donkeys. His concubine also was with him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "JDG 19:11"}, "When they were by Jebus, the day was far spent; and the servant said to his master, \u201cPlease come and let\u2019s enter into\nthis city of the Jebusites, and stay in it.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "JDG 19:12"}, "His master said to him, \u201cWe won\u2019t enter into the city of a foreigner that is not of the children of Israel; but we will\npass over to Gibeah.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "JDG 19:13"}, "He said to his servant, \u201cCome and let\u2019s draw near to one of these places; and we will lodge in Gibeah, or in Ramah.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "JDG 19:14"}, "So they passed on and went their way; and the sun went down on them near Gibeah, which belongs to Benjamin.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "JDG 19:15"}, "They went over there, to go in to stay in Gibeah. He went in, and sat down in the street of the city; for there was no\none who took them into his house to stay. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "JDG 19:16"}, "Behold, an old man came from his work out of the field at evening. Now the man was from the hill country of Ephraim, and\nhe lived in Gibeah; but the men of the place were Benjamites. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "JDG 19:17"}, "He lifted up his eyes, and saw the wayfaring man in the street of the city; and the old man said, \u201cWhere are you going?\nWhere did you come from?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "JDG 19:18"}, "He said to him, \u201cWe are passing from Bethlehem Judah to the farther side of the hill country of Ephraim. I am from there,\nand I went to Bethlehem Judah. I am going to the LORD\u2019s house; and there is no one who has taken me into his house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "JDG 19:19"}, "Yet there is both straw and feed for our donkeys; and there is bread and wine also for me, and for your servant, and for\nthe young man who is with your servants. There is no lack of anything.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "JDG 19:20"}, "The old man said, \u201cPeace be to you! Just let me supply all your needs, but don\u2019t sleep in the street.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "JDG 19:21"}, "So he brought him into his house, and gave the donkeys fodder. Then they washed their feet, and ate and drank.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "JDG 19:22"}, "As they were making their hearts merry, behold, the men of the city, certain wicked fellows, surrounded the house,\nbeating at the door; and they spoke to the master of the house, the old man, saying, \u201cBring out the man who came into your\nhouse, that we can have sex with him!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "JDG 19:23"}, "The man, the master of the house, went out to them, and said to them, \u201cNo, my brothers, please don\u2019t act so wickedly;\nsince this man has come into my house, don\u2019t do this folly. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "JDG 19:24"}, "Behold, here is my virgin daughter and his concubine. I will bring them out now. Humble them, and do with them what seems\ngood to you; but to this man don\u2019t do any such folly.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "JDG 19:25"}, "But the men wouldn\u2019t listen to him; so the man grabbed his concubine, and brought her out to them; and they had sex with\nher, and abused her all night until the morning. When the day began to dawn, they let her go.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "JDG 19:26"}, "Then the woman came in the dawning of the day, and fell down at the door of the man\u2019s house where her lord was, until it\nwas light. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "JDG 19:27"}, "Her lord rose up in the morning and opened the doors of the house, and went out to go his way; and behold, the woman his\nconcubine had fallen down at the door of the house, with her hands on the threshold.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "JDG 19:28"}, "He said to her, \u201cGet up, and let\u2019s get going!\u201d but no one answered. Then he took her up on the donkey; and the man rose\nup, and went to his place. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "JDG 19:29"}, "When he had come into his house, he took a knife and cut up his concubine, and divided her, limb by limb, into twelve\npieces, and sent her throughout all the borders of Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "JDG 19:30"}, "It was so, that all who saw it said, \u201cSuch a deed has not been done or seen from the day that the children of Israel came\nup out of the land of Egypt to this day! Consider it, take counsel, and speak.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "20", "sid": "JDG 20"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JDG 20:1"}, "Then all the children of Israel went out, and the congregation was assembled as one man, from Dan even to Beersheba, with\nthe land of Gilead, to the LORD at Mizpah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JDG 20:2"}, "The chiefs of all the people, even of all the tribes of Israel, presented themselves in the assembly of the people of\nAllah, four hundred thousand footmen who drew sword. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JDG 20:3"}, "(Now the children of Benjamin heard that the children of Israel had gone up to Mizpah.) The children of Israel said, \u201cTell\nus, how did this wickedness happen?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JDG 20:4"}, "The Levite, the husband of the woman who was murdered, answered, \u201cI came into Gibeah that belongs to Benjamin, I and my\nconcubine, to spend the night. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JDG 20:5"}, "The men of Gibeah rose against me, and surrounded the house by night. They intended to kill me and they raped my\nconcubine, and she is dead. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JDG 20:6"}, "I took my concubine and cut her in pieces, and sent her throughout all the country of the inheritance of Israel; for they\nhave committed lewdness and folly in Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JDG 20:7"}, "Behold, you children of Israel, all of you, give here your advice and counsel.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JDG 20:8"}, "All the people arose as one man, saying, \u201cNone of us will go to his tent, neither will any of us turn to his house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JDG 20:9"}, "But now this is the thing which we will do to Gibeah: we will go up against it by lot;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JDG 20:10"}, "and we will take ten men of one hundred throughout all the tribes of Israel, and one hundred of one thousand, and a\nthousand out of ten thousand to get food for the people, that they may do, when they come to Gibeah of Benjamin, according to\nall the folly that the men of Gibeah have done in Israel.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "JDG 20:11"}, "So all the men of Israel were gathered against the city, knit together as one man.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "JDG 20:12"}, "The tribes of Israel sent men through all the tribe of Benjamin, saying, \u201cWhat wickedness is this that has happened\namongst you? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "JDG 20:13"}, "Now therefore deliver up the men, the wicked fellows who are in Gibeah, that we may put them to death and put away evil\nfrom Israel.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["But Benjamin would not listen to the voice of their brothers, the children of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "JDG 20:14"}, "The children of Benjamin gathered themselves together out of the cities to Gibeah, to go out to battle against the\nchildren of Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "JDG 20:15"}, "The children of Benjamin were counted on that day out of the cities twenty-six thousand men who drew the sword, in\naddition to the inhabitants of Gibeah, who were counted seven hundred chosen men.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "JDG 20:16"}, "Amongst all these soldiers there were seven hundred chosen men who were left-handed. Every one of them could sling a\nstone at a hair and not miss. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "JDG 20:17"}, "The men of Israel, besides Benjamin, were counted four hundred thousand men who drew sword. All these were men of war.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "JDG 20:18"}, "The children of Israel arose, went up to Bethel, and asked counsel of Allah. They asked, \u201cWho shall go up for us first to\nbattle against the children of Benjamin?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The LORD said, \u201cJudah first.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "JDG 20:19"}, "The children of Israel rose up in the morning and encamped against Gibeah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "JDG 20:20"}, "The men of Israel went out to battle against Benjamin; and the men of Israel set the battle in array against them at\nGibeah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "JDG 20:21"}, "The children of Benjamin came out of Gibeah, and on that day destroyed twenty-two thousand of the Israelite men down to\nthe ground. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "JDG 20:22"}, "The people, the men of Israel, encouraged themselves, and set the battle again in array in the place where they set\nthemselves in array the first day. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "JDG 20:23"}, "The children of Israel went up and wept before the LORD until evening; and they asked of the LORD, saying, \u201cShall I again\ndraw near to battle against the children of Benjamin my brother?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The LORD said, \u201cGo up against him.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "JDG 20:24"}, "The children of Israel came near against the children of Benjamin the second day.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "JDG 20:25"}, "Benjamin went out against them out of Gibeah the second day, and destroyed down to the ground of the children of Israel\nagain eighteen thousand men. All these drew the sword. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "JDG 20:26"}, "Then all the children of Israel and all the people went up, and came to Bethel, and wept, and sat there before the LORD,\nand fasted that day until evening; then they offered burnt offerings and peace offerings before the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "JDG 20:27"}, "The children of Israel asked the LORD (for the ark of the covenant of Allah was there in those days,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "JDG 20:28"}, "and Phinehas, the son of Eleazar, the son of Harun, stood before it in those days), saying, \u201cShall I yet again go out to\nbattle against the children of Benjamin my brother, or shall I cease?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The LORD said, \u201cGo up; for tomorrow I will deliver him into your hand.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "JDG 20:29"}, "Israel set ambushes all around Gibeah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "JDG 20:30"}, "The children of Israel went up against the children of Benjamin on the third day, and set themselves in array against\nGibeah, as at other times. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "JDG 20:31"}, "The children of Benjamin went out against the people, and were drawn away from the city; and they began to strike and\nkill of the people as at other times, in the highways, of which one goes up to Bethel and the other to Gibeah, in the field,\nabout thirty men of Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "JDG 20:32"}, "The children of Benjamin said, \u201cThey are struck down before us, as at the first.\u201d But the children of Israel said, \u201cLet\u2019s\nflee, and draw them away from the city to the highways.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "JDG 20:33"}, "All the men of Israel rose up out of their place and set themselves in array at Baal Tamar. Then the ambushers of Israel\nbroke out of their place, even out of Maareh Geba. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "JDG 20:34"}, "Ten thousand chosen men out of all Israel came over against Gibeah, and the battle was severe; but they didn\u2019t know that\ndisaster was close to them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "JDG 20:35"}, "The LORD struck Benjamin before Israel; and the children of Israel destroyed of Benjamin that day twenty-five thousand\nand one hundred men. All these drew the sword. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "JDG 20:36"}, "So the children of Benjamin saw that they were struck, for the men of Israel yielded to Benjamin because they trusted the\nambushers whom they had set against Gibeah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "JDG 20:37"}, "The ambushers hurried, and rushed on Gibeah; then the ambushers spread out, and struck all the city with the edge of the\nsword. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "JDG 20:38"}, "Now the appointed sign between the men of Israel and the ambushers was that they should make a great cloud of smoke rise\nup out of the city. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "JDG 20:39"}, "The men of Israel turned in the battle, and Benjamin began to strike and kill of the men of Israel about thirty persons;\nfor they said, \u201cSurely they are struck down before us, as in the first battle.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "JDG 20:40"}, "But when the cloud began to arise up out of the city in a pillar of smoke, the Benjamites looked behind them; and behold,\nthe whole city went up in smoke to the sky. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "JDG 20:41"}, "The men of Israel turned, and the men of Benjamin were dismayed; for they saw that disaster had come on them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "JDG 20:42"}, "Therefore they turned their backs before the men of Israel to the way of the wilderness, but the battle followed hard\nafter them; and those who came out of the cities destroyed them in the middle of it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "JDG 20:43"}, "They surrounded the Benjamites, chased them, and trod them down at their resting place, as far as near Gibeah towards the\nsunrise. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "JDG 20:44"}, "Eighteen thousand men of Benjamin fell; all these were men of valour.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "JDG 20:45"}, "They turned and fled towards the wilderness to the rock of Rimmon. They gleaned five thousand men of them in the\nhighways, and followed hard after them to Gidom, and struck two thousand men of them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "JDG 20:46"}, "So that all who fell that day of Benjamin were twenty-five thousand men who drew the sword. All these were men of valour.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "JDG 20:47"}, "But six hundred men turned and fled towards the wilderness to the rock of Rimmon, and stayed in the rock of Rimmon four\nmonths. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "JDG 20:48"}, "The men of Israel turned again on the children of Benjamin, and struck them with the edge of the sword\u2014including the\nentire city, the livestock, and all that they found. Moreover they set all the cities which they found on fire.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "21", "sid": "JDG 21"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "JDG 21:1"}, "Now the men of Israel had sworn in Mizpah, saying, \u201cNone of us will give his daughter to Benjamin as a wife.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "JDG 21:2"}, "The people came to Bethel and sat there until evening before Allah, and lifted up their voices, and wept severely.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "JDG 21:3"}, "They said, \u201cThe LORD, Allah of Israel, why has this happened in Israel, that there should be one tribe lacking in Israel\ntoday?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "JDG 21:4"}, "On the next day, the people rose early and built an altar there, and offered burnt offerings and peace offerings.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "JDG 21:5"}, "The children of Israel said, \u201cWho is there amongst all the tribes of Israel who didn\u2019t come up in the assembly to the\nLORD?\u201d For they had made a great oath concerning him who didn\u2019t come up to the LORD to Mizpah, saying, \u201cHe shall surely be put\nto death.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "JDG 21:6"}, "The children of Israel grieved for Benjamin their brother, and said, \u201cThere is one tribe cut off from Israel today.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "JDG 21:7"}, "How shall we provide wives for those who remain, since we have sworn by the LORD that we will not give them of our\ndaughters to wives?\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "JDG 21:8"}, "They said, \u201cWhat one is there of the tribes of Israel who didn\u2019t come up to the LORD to Mizpah?\u201d Behold, no one came from\nJabesh Gilead to the camp to the assembly. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "JDG 21:9"}, "For when the people were counted, behold, there were none of the inhabitants of Jabesh Gilead there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "JDG 21:10"}, "The congregation sent twelve thousand of the most valiant men there, and commanded them, saying, \u201cGo and strike the\ninhabitants of Jabesh Gilead with the edge of the sword, with the women and the little ones.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "JDG 21:11"}, "This is the thing that you shall do: you shall utterly destroy every male, and every woman who has lain with a man.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "JDG 21:12"}, "They found amongst the inhabitants of Jabesh Gilead four hundred young virgins who had not known man by lying with him;\nand they brought them to the camp to Shiloh, which is in the land of Canaan.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "JDG 21:13"}, "The whole congregation sent and spoke to the children of Benjamin who were in the rock of Rimmon, and proclaimed peace to\nthem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "JDG 21:14"}, "Benjamin returned at that time; and they gave them the women whom they had saved alive of the women of Jabesh Gilead.\nThere still weren\u2019t enough for them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "JDG 21:15"}, "The people grieved for Benjamin, because the LORD had made a breach in the tribes of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "JDG 21:16"}, "Then the elders of the congregation said, \u201cHow shall we provide wives for those who remain, since the women are destroyed\nout of Benjamin?\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "JDG 21:17"}, "They said, \u201cThere must be an inheritance for those who are escaped of Benjamin, that a tribe not be blotted out from\nIsrael. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "JDG 21:18"}, "However, we may not give them wives of our daughters, for the children of Israel had sworn, saying, \u2018Cursed is he who\ngives a wife to Benjamin.\u2019\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "JDG 21:19"}, "They said, \u201cBehold, there is a feast of the LORD from year to year in Shiloh, which is on the north of Bethel, on the\neast side of the highway that goes up from Bethel to Shechem, and on the south of Lebonah.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "JDG 21:20"}, "They commanded the children of Benjamin, saying, \u201cGo and lie in wait in the vineyards,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "JDG 21:21"}, "and see, and behold, if the daughters of Shiloh come out to dance in the dances, then come out of the vineyards, and each\nman catch his wife of the daughters of Shiloh, and go to the land of Benjamin.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "JDG 21:22"}, "It shall be, when their fathers or their brothers come to complain to us, that we will say to them, \u2018Grant them\ngraciously to us, because we didn\u2019t take for each man his wife in battle, neither did you give them to them; otherwise you\nwould now be guilty.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "JDG 21:23"}, "The children of Benjamin did so, and took wives for themselves according to their number, of those who danced, whom they\ncarried off. They went and returned to their inheritance, built the cities, and lived in them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "JDG 21:24"}, "The children of Israel departed from there at that time, every man to his tribe and to his family, and they each went out\nfrom there to his own inheritance. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "JDG 21:25"}, "In those days there was no king in Israel. Everyone did that which was right in his own eyes.\n"]}]}